{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019aVBFSedMH24arxqqdpSK1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n     3→- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n     4→- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n     5→- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n     6→- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n     7→- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n     8→\n     9→---\n    10→\n    11→## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n    12→- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n    13→- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n    14→- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n    15→- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n    16→- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n    17→- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n    18→- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n    19→- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n    20→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    21→  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n    22→  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n    23→  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n    24→---\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9e31711-c3bf-4b68-98d9-5e8e172c7ee4","uuid":"dd90c566-85f6-46a2-b5bf-02a53bc3b711","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n---\n","numLines":25,"startLine":1,"totalLines":25}}}
