{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TBkLd4VEz1CRxtw8b5sK5v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n     3→- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n     4→- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n     5→- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n     6→- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n     7→- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n     8→\n     9→---\n    10→\n    11→## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n    12→- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n    13→- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n    14→- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n    15→- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n    16→- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n    17→- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n    18→- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n    19→- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n    20→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    21→  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n    22→  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n    23→  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n    24→---\n    25→\n    26→## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n    27→- Replaced old category accordion panel with two-column patchbay layout (Sounds + Events)\n    28→- Left column shows \"Sounds\" header with empty body (US-005 will populate)\n    29→- Right column shows all 16 AgentEventType rows; dimmed (`opacity-40`) when no assignments, full opacity when assigned\n    30→- Removed dead code: `sortedCategories`, `categoryAllEnabled`, `toggleCategoryEnabled`, `toggleCategory`, `expandedCategories`, `addFilesToCategory`, `deleteTrack`, `getFilePath`, `AudioPlayer` import\n    31→- Kept `remove` and `copyFile` imports removed (will be re-added in US-005/US-009)\n    32→- `hasAssignments(eventType)` reads from `selectedPackInfo.manifest.assignments`\n    33→- Info popovers migrated from category-based to event-type-based (same pattern)\n    34→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    35→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    36→  - The prd.json lives in the main repo dir (`/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/`), NOT in the worktree — edit it there\n    37→  - `rightPanel` ref now wraps the entire two-column area (the `flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden` div) — scroll reset via `rightPanel.scrollTop = 0` is preserved\n    38→  - The `confirmCreatePack` still creates old-style event subdirectories — US-010 will fix this to use manifest\n    39→---\n    40→\n    41→## 2026-03-04 - US-005\n    42→- Implemented left column sound file list with inline preview\n    43→- Each sound row: play button (▶), filename, broken-link indicator (⚠ in red), volume slider (on hover), enabled toggle (checkbox), stop button (■ active when playing)\n    44→- `playPreview(filename)` uses soundStore.loadBuffer + getOrCreateAudioContext, stops any current source first (restarts from start)\n    45→- `stopPreview()` stops the AudioBufferSourceNode safely (try/catch for already-stopped)\n    46→- `checkSoundFileExistence(packName)` async parallel check using `exists()` from plugin-fs, results in `soundFileExists` Map\n    47→- `updateSoundVolume/updateSoundEnabled` mutate the manifest.sounds entry in place (reactive through Pinia ref), then call `savePackManifest`\n    48→- Hover state tracked with `hoveredSoundFile` ref; volume slider uses `v-show` for visibility\n    49→- `watch(selectedPack)` extended: stops preview, clears existence map, triggers new existence check, resets scroll\n    50→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    51→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    52→  - `AudioBufferSourceNode.stop()` can throw if already stopped — always wrap in try/catch\n    53→  - `soundFileExists.value` must be a `ref<Map<...>>` not a reactive Map for `v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(x) === false\"` to be reactive\n    54→  - Mutating nested objects inside `packs.value[i].manifest.sounds[j]` IS reactive (Pinia wraps deeply)\n    55→  - `exists` must be imported from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` (already available in soundStore)\n    56→  - prd.json may have extra fields like `\"inProgress\": true` — clean them up when setting passes: true\n    57→---\n    58→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1314d513-0f86-4cdc-8c19-398084d74c3f","uuid":"cf5c5572-b6c9-4bf5-8534-84726a70a17c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n- Replaced old category accordion panel with two-column patchbay layout (Sounds + Events)\n- Left column shows \"Sounds\" header with empty body (US-005 will populate)\n- Right column shows all 16 AgentEventType rows; dimmed (`opacity-40`) when no assignments, full opacity when assigned\n- Removed dead code: `sortedCategories`, `categoryAllEnabled`, `toggleCategoryEnabled`, `toggleCategory`, `expandedCategories`, `addFilesToCategory`, `deleteTrack`, `getFilePath`, `AudioPlayer` import\n- Kept `remove` and `copyFile` imports removed (will be re-added in US-005/US-009)\n- `hasAssignments(eventType)` reads from `selectedPackInfo.manifest.assignments`\n- Info popovers migrated from category-based to event-type-based (same pattern)\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The prd.json lives in the main repo dir (`/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/`), NOT in the worktree — edit it there\n  - `rightPanel` ref now wraps the entire two-column area (the `flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden` div) — scroll reset via `rightPanel.scrollTop = 0` is preserved\n  - The `confirmCreatePack` still creates old-style event subdirectories — US-010 will fix this to use manifest\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-005\n- Implemented left column sound file list with inline preview\n- Each sound row: play button (▶), filename, broken-link indicator (⚠ in red), volume slider (on hover), enabled toggle (checkbox), stop button (■ active when playing)\n- `playPreview(filename)` uses soundStore.loadBuffer + getOrCreateAudioContext, stops any current source first (restarts from start)\n- `stopPreview()` stops the AudioBufferSourceNode safely (try/catch for already-stopped)\n- `checkSoundFileExistence(packName)` async parallel check using `exists()` from plugin-fs, results in `soundFileExists` Map\n- `updateSoundVolume/updateSoundEnabled` mutate the manifest.sounds entry in place (reactive through Pinia ref), then call `savePackManifest`\n- Hover state tracked with `hoveredSoundFile` ref; volume slider uses `v-show` for visibility\n- `watch(selectedPack)` extended: stops preview, clears existence map, triggers new existence check, resets scroll\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `AudioBufferSourceNode.stop()` can throw if already stopped — always wrap in try/catch\n  - `soundFileExists.value` must be a `ref<Map<...>>` not a reactive Map for `v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(x) === false\"` to be reactive\n  - Mutating nested objects inside `packs.value[i].manifest.sounds[j]` IS reactive (Pinia wraps deeply)\n  - `exists` must be imported from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` (already available in soundStore)\n  - prd.json may have extra fields like `\"inProgress\": true` — clean them up when setting passes: true\n---\n","numLines":58,"startLine":1,"totalLines":58}}}
