{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013pEAgs2Dp3fCXXM3UnzzW3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to implement US-007: Drag sound from left column to event row. The acceptance criteria are:\n\n1. Sound rows in left column are draggable (HTML5 drag API)\n2. During drag: ghost chip (translucent copy of filename chip) follows cursor\n3. During drag: valid drop targets (event rows) highlight on hover\n4. Drop onto event row: adds (file, event) to manifest.assignments if not already present; autosaves\n5. Drop on duplicate: silently ignored\n6. Drop outside valid target: no change\n\nLet me implement this using HTML5 drag and drop API.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9668,"cache_read_input_tokens":42911,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9668},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24b2318f-d36b-4c9a-8cd6-f0fe120243db","uuid":"48f57d9e-2c78-432d-8629-f8f876e7895c"}
