{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019NkLPWS5NyF9ME97eRMSE1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<script setup lang=\"ts\">\n     2→import {\n     3→  ref,\n     4→  computed,\n     5→  watch,\n     6→  nextTick,\n     7→  onMounted,\n     8→  onUnmounted,\n     9→} from 'vue';\n    10→import { listen } from '@tauri-apps/api/event';\n    11→import type { UnlistenFn } from '@tauri-apps/api/event';\n    12→import { open } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';\n    13→import {\n    14→  mkdir,\n    15→  readFile,\n    16→  writeFile,\n    17→  exists,\n    18→} from '@tauri-apps/plugin-fs';\n    19→import JSZip from 'jszip';\n    20→import { useSoundStore, AGENT_EVENT_TYPES } from '../stores/soundStore';\n    21→import type { PackManifestSound } from '../stores/soundStore';\n    22→import type { AgentEvent, AgentEventType } from '../drivers/types';\n    23→import PackContextMenu from './PackContextMenu.vue';\n    24→\n    25→const emit = defineEmits<{ close: [] }>();\n    26→\n    27→const soundStore = useSoundStore();\n    28→\n    29→// ---- Global settings ----\n    30→const globalEnabled = computed({\n    31→  get: () => soundStore.config.enabled,\n    32→  set: (v: boolean) => { soundStore.config.enabled = v; void soundStore.saveConfig(); },\n    33→});\n    34→const globalVolume = computed({\n    35→  get: () => Math.round(soundStore.config.globalVolume * 100),\n    36→  set: (v: number) => { soundStore.config.globalVolume = v / 100; void soundStore.saveConfig(); },\n    37→});\n    38→const cooldown = computed({\n    39→  get: () => soundStore.config.cooldownSeconds,\n    40→  set: (v: number) => { soundStore.config.cooldownSeconds = v; void soundStore.saveConfig(); },\n    41→});\n    42→\n    43→// ---- Pack list ----\n    44→const selectedPack = ref<string | null>(null);\n    45→const rightPanel = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);\n    46→\n    47→onMounted(async () => {\n    48→  await soundStore.init();\n    49→  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n    50→  if (soundStore.packs.length > 0 && soundStore.packs[0]) {\n    51→    selectedPack.value = soundStore.packs[0].name;\n    52→  }\n    53→  agentEventUnlisten = await listen<string>(\n    54→    'agent-event',\n    55→    (e) => {\n    56→      try {\n    57→        const parsed = JSON.parse(e.payload) as AgentEvent;\n    58→        flashEventRow(parsed.type);\n    59→      } catch { /* ignore parse errors */ }\n    60→    },\n    61→  );\n    62→});\n    63→\n    64→onUnmounted(() => {\n    65→  if (agentEventUnlisten) agentEventUnlisten();\n    66→  if (flashTimeout) clearTimeout(flashTimeout);\n    67→});\n    68→\n    69→function isPackActive(packName: string): boolean {\n    70→  return soundStore.config.activePacks.includes(packName);\n    71→}\n    72→\n    73→function togglePackActive(packName: string, active: boolean) {\n    74→  if (active) {\n    75→    if (!soundStore.config.activePacks.includes(packName)) {\n    76→      soundStore.config.activePacks.push(packName);\n    77→    }\n    78→  } else {\n    79→    soundStore.config.activePacks = soundStore.config.activePacks.filter(\n    80→      (p) => p !== packName,\n    81→    );\n    82→  }\n    83→  void soundStore.saveConfig();\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→function selectPack(name: string) {\n    87→  selectedPack.value = name;\n    88→  void nextTick(() => {\n    89→    if (rightPanel.value) rightPanel.value.scrollTop = 0;\n    90→  });\n    91→}\n    92→\n    93→// ---- Context menu ----\n    94→const ctxMenu = ref<{ packName: string; x: number; y: number } | null>(null);\n    95→\n    96→function onPackRightClick(e: MouseEvent, packName: string) {\n    97→  e.preventDefault();\n    98→  ctxMenu.value = { packName, x: e.clientX, y: e.clientY };\n    99→}\n   100→\n   101→function closeCtxMenu() {\n   102→  ctxMenu.value = null;\n   103→}\n   104→\n   105→async function onPackRenamed(oldName: string, newName: string) {\n   106→  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n   107→  if (selectedPack.value === oldName) selectedPack.value = newName;\n   108→  closeCtxMenu();\n   109→}\n   110→\n   111→async function onPackDuplicated() {\n   112→  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n   113→  closeCtxMenu();\n   114→}\n   115→\n   116→async function onPackDeleted(name: string) {\n   117→  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n   118→  if (selectedPack.value === name) {\n   119→    selectedPack.value = soundStore.packs[0]?.name ?? null;\n   120→  }\n   121→  closeCtxMenu();\n   122→}\n   123→\n   124→// ---- New pack ----\n   125→const newPackName = ref('');\n   126→const creatingPack = ref(false);\n   127→const newPackInput = ref<HTMLInputElement | null>(null);\n   128→\n   129→function startCreatePack() {\n   130→  creatingPack.value = true;\n   131→  newPackName.value = '';\n   132→  void nextTick(() => newPackInput.value?.focus());\n   133→}\n   134→\n   135→function cancelCreatePack() {\n   136→  creatingPack.value = false;\n   137→  newPackName.value = '';\n   138→}\n   139→\n   140→async function confirmCreatePack() {\n   141→  const packName = newPackName.value.trim();\n   142→  if (!packName) return;\n   143→  creatingPack.value = false;\n   144→  newPackName.value = '';\n   145→  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n   146→  const packPath = `${baseDir}/${packName}`;\n   147→  try {\n   148→    await mkdir(packPath, { recursive: true });\n   149→    for (const eventType of AGENT_EVENT_TYPES) {\n   150→      await mkdir(`${packPath}/${eventType}`, { recursive: true });\n   151→    }\n   152→    await soundStore.scanPacks();\n   153→    selectedPack.value = packName;\n   154→  } catch (err) {\n   155→    console.error('[SoundsDialog] createNewPack failed', err);\n   156→  }\n   157→}\n   158→\n   159→// ---- Import zip ----\n   160→const dragOver = ref(false);\n   161→\n   162→async function importZipBytes(filename: string, bytes: Uint8Array): Promise<void> {\n   163→  const dotIdx = filename.lastIndexOf('.');\n   164→  const packName = dotIdx > 0 ? filename.slice(0, dotIdx) : filename;\n   165→  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n   166→  const packPath = `${baseDir}/${packName}`;\n   167→\n   168→  const zip = await JSZip.loadAsync(bytes);\n   169→  for (const [relativePath, file] of Object.entries(zip.files)) {\n   170→    if (file.dir) {\n   171→      await mkdir(`${packPath}/${relativePath}`, { recursive: true });\n   172→    } else {\n   173→      const data = await file.async('uint8array');\n   174→      const dirPart = relativePath.includes('/')\n   175→        ? relativePath.slice(0, relativePath.lastIndexOf('/'))\n   176→        : '';\n   177→      if (dirPart) {\n   178→        await mkdir(`${packPath}/${dirPart}`, { recursive: true });\n   179→      }\n   180→      await writeFile(`${packPath}/${relativePath}`, data);\n   181→    }\n   182→  }\n   183→\n   184→  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n   185→  selectedPack.value = packName;\n   186→}\n   187→\n   188→async function openImportPicker() {\n   189→  const result = await open({\n   190→    filters: [{ name: 'ZIP', extensions: ['zip'] }],\n   191→    multiple: false,\n   192→  });\n   193→  if (!result) return;\n   194→  const filePath = typeof result === 'string' ? result : result;\n   195→  if (!filePath) return;\n   196→  try {\n   197→    const bytes = await readFile(filePath);\n   198→    const filename = (filePath as string).split('/').pop() ?? 'pack.zip';\n   199→    await importZipBytes(filename, bytes);\n   200→  } catch (err) {\n   201→    console.error('[SoundsDialog] import failed', err);\n   202→  }\n   203→}\n   204→\n   205→function onDragOver(e: DragEvent) {\n   206→  e.preventDefault();\n   207→  dragOver.value = true;\n   208→}\n   209→\n   210→function onDragLeave() {\n   211→  dragOver.value = false;\n   212→}\n   213→\n   214→async function onDrop(e: DragEvent) {\n   215→  e.preventDefault();\n   216→  dragOver.value = false;\n   217→  const file = e.dataTransfer?.files[0];\n   218→  if (!file) return;\n   219→  try {\n   220→    const arrayBuffer = await file.arrayBuffer();\n   221→    await importZipBytes(file.name, new Uint8Array(arrayBuffer));\n   222→  } catch (err) {\n   223→    console.error('[SoundsDialog] drop import failed', err);\n   224→  }\n   225→}\n   226→\n   227→// ---- Event descriptions ----\n   228→const EVENT_DESCRIPTIONS: Record<string, string> = {\n   229→  session_start: 'Agent session begins.',\n   230→  session_end: 'Agent session ends or is interrupted.',\n   231→  prompt_submit: 'User submits a prompt to the agent.',\n   232→  tool_start: 'Agent begins executing a tool (e.g. Bash, Read, Edit).',\n   233→  tool_end: 'Agent finishes executing a tool.',\n   234→  turn_end: 'Agent completes a full response turn.',\n   235→  permission_wait: 'Agent pauses waiting for the user to approve a tool call.',\n   236→  subagent_start: 'A subagent is spawned by the parent agent.',\n   237→  subagent_end: 'A subagent finishes its work.',\n   238→  idle_notification: 'Agent has been idle and sends a nudge notification.',\n   239→  elicitation_wait: 'Agent pauses waiting for user input.',\n   240→  auth_success: 'Authentication to an external service succeeds.',\n   241→  worktree_create: 'A new git worktree is created.',\n   242→  worktree_remove: 'A git worktree is removed.',\n   243→  teammate_idle: \"A teammate's agent session goes idle.\",\n   244→  task_completed: 'Agent marks a task as completed.',\n   245→};\n   246→\n   247→const activeInfoPopover = ref<string | null>(null);\n   248→\n   249→function toggleInfoPopover(eventType: string) {\n   250→  activeInfoPopover.value = activeInfoPopover.value === eventType ? null : eventType;\n   251→}\n   252→\n   253→// ---- Patchbay data ----\n   254→const selectedPackInfo = computed(() =>\n   255→  soundStore.packs.find((p) => p.name === selectedPack.value) ?? null,\n   256→);\n   257→\n   258→function hasAssignments(eventType: AgentEventType): boolean {\n   259→  if (!selectedPackInfo.value) return false;\n   260→  return selectedPackInfo.value.manifest.assignments.some((a) => a.event === eventType);\n   261→}\n   262→\n   263→// ---- Sound preview (left column) ----\n   264→let previewSource: AudioBufferSourceNode | null = null;\n   265→const previewFile = ref<string | null>(null);\n   266→const soundFileExists = ref<Map<string, boolean>>(new Map());\n   267→const hoveredSoundFile = ref<string | null>(null);\n   268→\n   269→async function checkSoundFileExistence(packName: string): Promise<void> {\n   270→  const sounds = selectedPackInfo.value?.manifest.sounds ?? [];\n   271→  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n   272→  const newMap = new Map<string, boolean>();\n   273→  await Promise.all(\n   274→    sounds.map(async (sound) => {\n   275→      const filePath = `${baseDir}/${packName}/${sound.file}`;\n   276→      const fileExists = await exists(filePath);\n   277→      newMap.set(sound.file, fileExists);\n   278→    }),\n   279→  );\n   280→  soundFileExists.value = newMap;\n   281→}\n   282→\n   283→function stopPreview(): void {\n   284→  if (previewSource) {\n   285→    try { previewSource.stop(); } catch { /* already stopped */ }\n   286→    previewSource = null;\n   287→  }\n   288→  previewFile.value = null;\n   289→}\n   290→\n   291→async function playPreview(filename: string): Promise<void> {\n   292→  if (!selectedPack.value) return;\n   293→  stopPreview();\n   294→  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n   295→  const filePath = `${baseDir}/${selectedPack.value}/${filename}`;\n   296→  const buffer = await soundStore.loadBuffer(filePath);\n   297→  if (!buffer) return;\n   298→  const ctx = soundStore.getOrCreateAudioContext();\n   299→  const sound = selectedPackInfo.value?.manifest.sounds.find((s) => s.file === filename);\n   300→  const gainNode = ctx.createGain();\n   301→  gainNode.gain.value =\n   302→    soundStore.config.globalVolume * soundStore.effectiveVolume(selectedPack.value, filename, sound);\n   303→  gainNode.connect(ctx.destination);\n   304→  const source = ctx.createBufferSource();\n   305→  source.buffer = buffer;\n   306→  source.connect(gainNode);\n   307→  previewFile.value = filename;\n   308→  previewSource = source;\n   309→  source.onended = () => {\n   310→    if (previewFile.value === filename) {\n   311→      previewFile.value = null;\n   312→      previewSource = null;\n   313→    }\n   314→  };\n   315→  source.start();\n   316→}\n   317→\n   318→async function updateSoundVolume(sound: PackManifestSound, volume: number): Promise<void> {\n   319→  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n   320→  sound.volume = volume;\n   321→  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, selectedPackInfo.value.manifest);\n   322→}\n   323→\n   324→async function updateSoundEnabled(sound: PackManifestSound, enabled: boolean): Promise<void> {\n   325→  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n   326→  sound.enabled = enabled;\n   327→  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, selectedPackInfo.value.manifest);\n   328→}\n   329→\n   330→// ---- Assignment chips (right column) ----\n   331→function assignmentsForEvent(eventType: AgentEventType): string[] {\n   332→  if (!selectedPackInfo.value) return [];\n   333→  return selectedPackInfo.value.manifest.assignments\n   334→    .filter((a) => a.event === eventType)\n   335→    .map((a) => a.file);\n   336→}\n   337→\n   338→function truncateFilename(name: string, max = 20): string {\n   339→  if (name.length <= max) return name;\n   340→  return name.slice(0, max - 1) + '\\u2026';\n   341→}\n   342→\n   343→async function removeAssignment(\n   344→  file: string,\n   345→  eventType: AgentEventType,\n   346→): Promise<void> {\n   347→  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n   348→  const manifest = selectedPackInfo.value.manifest;\n   349→  manifest.assignments = manifest.assignments.filter(\n   350→    (a) => !(a.file === file && a.event === eventType),\n   351→  );\n   352→  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, manifest);\n   353→}\n   354→\n   355→// ---- Drag-and-drop: sound → event row ----\n   356→const draggingSoundFile = ref<string | null>(null);\n   357→const dragOverEventType = ref<AgentEventType | null>(null);\n   358→\n   359→// ---- Drag-and-drop: chip → sound row (re-assign) ----\n   360→const draggingChip = ref<{ file: string; event: AgentEventType } | null>(null);\n   361→const dragOverSoundFile = ref<string | null>(null);\n   362→\n   363→function onSoundDragStart(e: DragEvent, filename: string): void {\n   364→  draggingSoundFile.value = filename;\n   365→  if (e.dataTransfer) {\n   366→    e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = 'copy';\n   367→    e.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', filename);\n   368→  }\n   369→}\n   370→\n   371→function onSoundDragEnd(): void {\n   372→  draggingSoundFile.value = null;\n   373→  dragOverEventType.value = null;\n   374→}\n   375→\n   376→function onEventDragOver(e: DragEvent, eventType: AgentEventType): void {\n   377→  if (!draggingSoundFile.value) return;\n   378→  e.preventDefault();\n   379→  if (e.dataTransfer) e.dataTransfer.dropEffect = 'copy';\n   380→  dragOverEventType.value = eventType;\n   381→}\n   382→\n   383→function onEventDragLeaveRow(): void {\n   384→  dragOverEventType.value = null;\n   385→}\n   386→\n   387→async function onEventDrop(\n   388→  e: DragEvent,\n   389→  eventType: AgentEventType,\n   390→): Promise<void> {\n   391→  e.preventDefault();\n   392→  dragOverEventType.value = null;\n   393→  const file = draggingSoundFile.value;\n   394→  draggingSoundFile.value = null;\n   395→  if (!file) return;\n   396→  await addAssignment(file, eventType);\n   397→}\n   398→\n   399→async function addAssignment(\n   400→  file: string,\n   401→  eventType: AgentEventType,\n   402→): Promise<void> {\n   403→  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n   404→  const manifest = selectedPackInfo.value.manifest;\n   405→  const alreadyExists = manifest.assignments.some(\n   406→    (a) => a.file === file && a.event === eventType,\n   407→  );\n   408→  if (alreadyExists) return;\n   409→  manifest.assignments.push({ file, event: eventType });\n   410→  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, manifest);\n   411→}\n   412→\n   413→// ---- Chip drag handlers (re-assign chip to different sound) ----\n   414→function onChipDragStart(\n   415→  e: DragEvent,\n   416→  file: string,\n   417→  eventType: AgentEventType,\n   418→): void {\n   419→  draggingChip.value = { file, event: eventType };\n   420→  if (e.dataTransfer) {\n   421→    e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = 'move';\n   422→    e.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', file);\n   423→  }\n   424→}\n   425→\n   426→function onChipDragEnd(): void {\n   427→  draggingChip.value = null;\n   428→  dragOverSoundFile.value = null;\n   429→}\n   430→\n   431→function onSoundRowDragOver(e: DragEvent, filename: string): void {\n   432→  if (!draggingChip.value) return;\n   433→  e.preventDefault();\n   434→  if (e.dataTransfer) e.dataTransfer.dropEffect = 'move';\n   435→  dragOverSoundFile.value = filename;\n   436→}\n   437→\n   438→function onSoundRowDragLeave(): void {\n   439→  dragOverSoundFile.value = null;\n   440→}\n   441→\n   442→async function onSoundRowDrop(\n   443→  e: DragEvent,\n   444→  newFile: string,\n   445→): Promise<void> {\n   446→  e.preventDefault();\n   447→  dragOverSoundFile.value = null;\n   448→  const chip = draggingChip.value;\n   449→  draggingChip.value = null;\n   450→  if (!chip || !selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n   451→  if (chip.file === newFile) return;\n   452→  const manifest = selectedPackInfo.value.manifest;\n   453→  manifest.assignments = manifest.assignments.filter(\n   454→    (a) => !(a.file === chip.file && a.event === chip.event),\n   455→  );\n   456→  const alreadyExists = manifest.assignments.some(\n   457→    (a) => a.file === newFile && a.event === chip.event,\n   458→  );\n   459→  if (!alreadyExists) {\n   460→    manifest.assignments.push({ file: newFile, event: chip.event });\n   461→  }\n   462→  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, manifest);\n   463→}\n   464→\n   465→// ---- Live highlight on incoming agent events ----\n   466→const flashingEvent = ref<AgentEventType | null>(null);\n   467→let flashTimeout: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null;\n   468→let agentEventUnlisten: UnlistenFn | null = null;\n   469→\n   470→function flashEventRow(eventType: AgentEventType): void {\n   471→  flashingEvent.value = eventType;\n   472→  if (flashTimeout) clearTimeout(flashTimeout);\n   473→  flashTimeout = setTimeout(() => {\n   474→    flashingEvent.value = null;\n   475→    flashTimeout = null;\n   476→  }, 200);\n   477→}\n   478→\n   479→// Reset scroll + stop preview + check file existence on pack change\n   480→watch(selectedPack, async (packName) => {\n   481→  stopPreview();\n   482→  soundFileExists.value = new Map();\n   483→  if (packName) void checkSoundFileExistence(packName);\n   484→  await nextTick(() => {\n   485→    if (rightPanel.value) rightPanel.value.scrollTop = 0;\n   486→  });\n   487→});\n   488→\n   489→</script>\n   490→\n   491→<template>\n   492→  <Teleport to=\"body\">\n   493→    <!-- Backdrop -->\n   494→    <div class=\"fixed inset-0 z-[100] flex items-center justify-center bg-black/50\">\n   495→      <!-- Drop zone wrapper -->\n   496→      <div\n   497→        class=\"relative w-[960px] max-w-[90vw] h-[700px] max-h-[90vh] flex flex-col bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden\"\n   498→        @dragover=\"onDragOver\"\n   499→        @dragleave=\"onDragLeave\"\n   500→        @drop=\"onDrop\"\n   501→      >\n   502→        <!-- Drag overlay -->\n   503→        <div\n   504→          v-if=\"dragOver\"\n   505→          class=\"absolute inset-0 z-[150] flex items-center justify-center bg-indigo-900/80 border-2 border-dashed border-indigo-400 rounded-lg pointer-events-none\"\n   506→        >\n   507→          <span class=\"text-indigo-200 text-lg font-semibold\">Drop sound pack here</span>\n   508→        </div>\n   509→\n   510→        <!-- Header -->\n   511→        <div class=\"flex items-center gap-4 px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n   512→          <span class=\"text-gray-200 font-semibold text-sm\">Sounds</span>\n   513→\n   514→          <!-- Master enable -->\n   515→          <label class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-300 cursor-pointer\">\n   516→            <input\n   517→              type=\"checkbox\"\n   518→              :checked=\"globalEnabled\"\n   519→              class=\"w-4 h-4 accent-indigo-400\"\n   520→              @change=\"globalEnabled = ($event.target as HTMLInputElement).checked\"\n   521→            />\n   522→            Enable\n   523→          </label>\n   524→\n   525→          <!-- Global volume -->\n   526→          <label class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-300\">\n   527→            Vol\n   528→            <input\n   529→              type=\"range\"\n   530→              min=\"0\"\n   531→              max=\"100\"\n   532→              :value=\"globalVolume\"\n   533→              class=\"w-24 accent-indigo-400\"\n   534→              @input=\"globalVolume = parseInt(($event.target as HTMLInputElement).value)\"\n   535→            />\n   536→            <span class=\"w-7 tabular-nums\">{{ globalVolume }}%</span>\n   537→          </label>\n   538→\n   539→          <!-- Cooldown -->\n   540→          <label class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-300\">\n   541→            Cooldown\n   542→            <input\n   543→              type=\"range\"\n   544→              min=\"0\"\n   545→              max=\"10\"\n   546→              step=\"0.5\"\n   547→              :value=\"cooldown\"\n   548→              class=\"w-20 accent-indigo-400\"\n   549→              @input=\"cooldown = parseFloat(($event.target as HTMLInputElement).value)\"\n   550→            />\n   551→            <span class=\"w-8 tabular-nums\">{{ cooldown }}s</span>\n   552→          </label>\n   553→        </div>\n   554→\n   555→        <!-- Body -->\n   556→        <div class=\"flex flex-1 min-h-0\">\n   557→          <!-- Left panel: pack list -->\n   558→          <div class=\"w-60 shrink-0 border-r border-gray-700 flex flex-col\">\n   559→            <div class=\"px-3 pt-2 pb-1 text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide\">\n   560→              Packs\n   561→            </div>\n   562→            <div class=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto\">\n   563→              <div\n   564→                v-for=\"pack in soundStore.packs\"\n   565→                :key=\"pack.name\"\n   566→                class=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-2 py-1.5 cursor-pointer rounded mx-1\"\n   567→                :class=\"selectedPack === pack.name ? 'bg-gray-700' : 'hover:bg-gray-800'\"\n   568→                @click=\"selectPack(pack.name)\"\n   569→                @contextmenu=\"onPackRightClick($event, pack.name)\"\n   570→              >\n   571→                <input\n   572→                  type=\"checkbox\"\n   573→                  :checked=\"isPackActive(pack.name)\"\n   574→                  class=\"w-4 h-4 accent-indigo-400 cursor-pointer\"\n   575→                  @click.stop\n   576→                  @change=\"togglePackActive(pack.name, ($event.target as HTMLInputElement).checked)\"\n   577→                />\n   578→                <span class=\"text-sm text-gray-200 truncate flex-1\">{{ pack.name }}</span>\n   579→              </div>\n   580→            </div>\n   581→            <!-- Buttons / new pack input -->\n   582→            <div class=\"flex flex-col gap-1 p-2 border-t border-gray-700\">\n   583→              <div v-if=\"creatingPack\" class=\"flex gap-1\">\n   584→                <input\n   585→                  ref=\"newPackInput\"\n   586→                  v-model=\"newPackName\"\n   587→                  class=\"flex-1 px-2 py-1 bg-gray-800 border border-gray-600 rounded text-xs text-gray-200 outline-none focus:border-indigo-400\"\n   588→                  placeholder=\"Pack name…\"\n   589→                  @keydown.enter=\"confirmCreatePack\"\n   590→                  @keydown.escape=\"cancelCreatePack\"\n   591→                />\n   592→                <button\n   593→                  class=\"px-2 py-1 bg-indigo-600/80 rounded hover:bg-indigo-500 text-xs text-white\"\n   594→                  @click=\"confirmCreatePack\"\n   595→                >OK</button>\n   596→              </div>\n   597→              <div class=\"flex gap-1\">\n   598→                <button\n   599→                  class=\"flex-1 px-2 py-1 bg-gray-700/60 rounded hover:bg-gray-600/70 text-xs text-gray-200\"\n   600→                  @click=\"startCreatePack\"\n   601→                >\n   602→                  New Pack\n   603→                </button>\n   604→                <button\n   605→                  class=\"flex-1 px-2 py-1 bg-gray-700/60 rounded hover:bg-gray-600/70 text-xs text-gray-200\"\n   606→                  @click=\"openImportPicker\"\n   607→                >\n   608→                  Import\n   609→                </button>\n   610→              </div>\n   611→            </div>\n   612→          </div>\n   613→\n   614→          <!-- Patchbay: Sounds + Events columns -->\n   615→          <div ref=\"rightPanel\" class=\"flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden\">\n   616→            <!-- Sounds column -->\n   617→            <div class=\"flex-1 border-r border-gray-700 flex flex-col min-w-0\">\n   618→              <div class=\"px-3 py-2 border-b border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n   619→                <span class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide\">Sounds</span>\n   620→              </div>\n   621→              <div class=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto\">\n   622→                <div\n   623→                  v-if=\"!selectedPackInfo\"\n   624→                  class=\"flex items-center justify-center h-full text-gray-600 text-sm\"\n   625→                >\n   626→                  Select a pack\n   627→                </div>\n   628→                <div\n   629→                  v-else-if=\"selectedPackInfo.manifest.sounds.length === 0\"\n   630→                  class=\"flex items-center justify-center h-full text-gray-600 text-sm\"\n   631→                >\n   632→                  No sounds in this pack\n   633→                </div>\n   634→                <div\n   635→                  v-for=\"sound in selectedPackInfo.manifest.sounds\"\n   636→                  v-else\n   637→                  :key=\"sound.file\"\n   638→                  draggable=\"true\"\n   639→                  class=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 border-b border-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-800/40 cursor-grab transition-colors duration-150\"\n   640→                  :class=\"[\n   641→                    draggingSoundFile === sound.file ? 'opacity-50' : '',\n   642→                    dragOverSoundFile === sound.file ? 'bg-indigo-500/20' : '',\n   643→                    draggingChip ? 'opacity-100' : '',\n   644→                  ]\"\n   645→                  @mouseenter=\"hoveredSoundFile = sound.file\"\n   646→                  @mouseleave=\"hoveredSoundFile = null\"\n   647→                  @dragstart=\"onSoundDragStart($event, sound.file)\"\n   648→                  @dragend=\"onSoundDragEnd\"\n   649→                  @dragover=\"onSoundRowDragOver($event, sound.file)\"\n   650→                  @dragleave=\"onSoundRowDragLeave\"\n   651→                  @drop=\"onSoundRowDrop($event, sound.file)\"\n   652→                >\n   653→                  <!-- Play button -->\n   654→                  <button\n   655→                    class=\"shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded text-gray-400 hover:text-white hover:bg-gray-700 text-xs\"\n   656→                    title=\"Play preview\"\n   657→                    @click=\"playPreview(sound.file)\"\n   658→                  >▶</button>\n   659→\n   660→                  <!-- Filename -->\n   661→                  <span class=\"flex-1 text-xs font-mono text-gray-200 truncate min-w-0\">{{ sound.file }}</span>\n   662→\n   663→                  <!-- Broken link indicator -->\n   664→                  <span\n   665→                    v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(sound.file) === false\"\n   666→                    class=\"shrink-0 text-red-400 text-xs\"\n   667→                    title=\"File not found on disk\"\n   668→                  >⚠</span>\n   669→\n   670→                  <!-- Volume slider (visible on hover) -->\n   671→                  <input\n   672→                    v-show=\"hoveredSoundFile === sound.file\"\n   673→                    type=\"range\"\n   674→                    min=\"0\"\n   675→                    max=\"1\"\n   676→                    step=\"0.01\"\n   677→                    :value=\"sound.volume\"\n   678→                    class=\"shrink-0 w-16 accent-indigo-400\"\n   679→                    title=\"Volume\"\n   680→                    @input=\"updateSoundVolume(sound, parseFloat(($event.target as HTMLInputElement).value))\"\n   681→                  />\n   682→\n   683→                  <!-- Enabled toggle -->\n   684→                  <input\n   685→                    type=\"checkbox\"\n   686→                    :checked=\"sound.enabled\"\n   687→                    class=\"shrink-0 w-4 h-4 accent-indigo-400 cursor-pointer\"\n   688→                    title=\"Enable/disable this sound\"\n   689→                    @change=\"updateSoundEnabled(sound, ($event.target as HTMLInputElement).checked)\"\n   690→                  />\n   691→\n   692→                  <!-- Stop button -->\n   693→                  <button\n   694→                    class=\"shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded text-xs\"\n   695→                    :class=\"previewFile === sound.file\n   696→                      ? 'text-red-400 hover:text-red-300 hover:bg-gray-700'\n   697→                      : 'text-gray-600 cursor-default'\"\n   698→                    title=\"Stop preview\"\n   699→                    @click=\"previewFile === sound.file ? stopPreview() : undefined\"\n   700→                  >■</button>\n   701→                </div>\n   702→              </div>\n   703→            </div>\n   704→\n   705→            <!-- Events column -->\n   706→            <div class=\"flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0\">\n   707→              <div class=\"px-3 py-2 border-b border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n   708→                <span class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide\">Events</span>\n   709→              </div>\n   710→              <div class=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto\">\n   711→                <div\n   712→                  v-for=\"eventType in AGENT_EVENT_TYPES\"\n   713→                  :key=\"eventType\"\n   714→                  class=\"px-3 py-2 border-b border-gray-800 transition-all duration-200\"\n   715→                  :class=\"[\n   716→                    hasAssignments(eventType) ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-40',\n   717→                    flashingEvent === eventType ? 'bg-indigo-600/30' : '',\n   718→                    dragOverEventType === eventType ? 'bg-indigo-500/20 opacity-100' : '',\n   719→                    draggingSoundFile ? 'opacity-100' : '',\n   720→                  ]\"\n   721→                  @dragover=\"onEventDragOver($event, eventType)\"\n   722→                  @dragleave=\"onEventDragLeaveRow\"\n   723→                  @drop=\"onEventDrop($event, eventType)\"\n   724→                >\n   725→                  <div class=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n   726→                    <span class=\"text-sm font-mono text-gray-300 flex-1\">{{ eventType }}</span>\n   727→                    <!-- Info icon + popover -->\n   728→                    <span\n   729→                      v-if=\"EVENT_DESCRIPTIONS[eventType]\"\n   730→                      class=\"relative shrink-0\"\n   731→                      @click.stop\n   732→                    >\n   733→                      <span\n   734→                        class=\"w-4 h-4 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border text-[10px] leading-none cursor-pointer select-none\"\n   735→                        :class=\"activeInfoPopover === eventType\n   736→                          ? 'border-indigo-400 text-indigo-300 bg-indigo-900/40'\n   737→                          : 'border-gray-500 text-gray-400 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-200'\"\n   738→                        @click=\"toggleInfoPopover(eventType)\"\n   739→                      >i</span>\n   740→                      <div\n   741→                        v-if=\"activeInfoPopover === eventType\"\n   742→                        class=\"absolute right-0 top-6 z-50 w-56 bg-gray-800 border border-gray-600 rounded shadow-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs text-gray-200 leading-relaxed\"\n   743→                      >\n   744→                        {{ EVENT_DESCRIPTIONS[eventType] }}\n   745→                      </div>\n   746→                    </span>\n   747→                  </div>\n   748→                  <!-- Assignment chips -->\n   749→                  <div\n   750→                    v-if=\"assignmentsForEvent(eventType).length > 0\"\n   751→                    class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-1 mt-1\"\n   752→                  >\n   753→                    <span\n   754→                      v-for=\"file in assignmentsForEvent(eventType)\"\n   755→                      :key=\"file\"\n   756→                      draggable=\"true\"\n   757→                      class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 bg-gray-700/80 rounded text-xs text-gray-200 cursor-grab hover:bg-gray-600/80\"\n   758→                      :class=\"draggingChip?.file === file && draggingChip?.event === eventType ? 'opacity-50' : ''\"\n   759→                      :title=\"file\"\n   760→                      @click=\"playPreview(file)\"\n   761→                      @dragstart.stop=\"onChipDragStart($event, file, eventType)\"\n   762→                      @dragend=\"onChipDragEnd\"\n   763→                    >\n   764→                      {{ truncateFilename(file) }}\n   765→                      <button\n   766→                        class=\"ml-0.5 text-gray-400 hover:text-red-400 leading-none\"\n   767→                        title=\"Remove assignment\"\n   768→                        @click.stop=\"removeAssignment(file, eventType)\"\n   769→                      >&times;</button>\n   770→                    </span>\n   771→                  </div>\n   772→                </div>\n   773→              </div>\n   774→            </div>\n   775→          </div>\n   776→        </div>\n   777→\n   778→        <!-- Footer -->\n   779→        <div class=\"flex justify-end px-4 py-3 border-t border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n   780→          <button\n   781→            class=\"px-4 py-1.5 bg-gray-700/60 rounded hover:bg-gray-600/70 text-sm text-gray-200\"\n   782→            @click=\"emit('close')\"\n   783→          >\n   784→            Close\n   785→          </button>\n   786→        </div>\n   787→      </div>\n   788→    </div>\n   789→\n   790→    <!-- Context menu -->\n   791→    <PackContextMenu\n   792→      v-if=\"ctxMenu\"\n   793→      :pack-name=\"ctxMenu.packName\"\n   794→      :x=\"ctxMenu.x\"\n   795→      :y=\"ctxMenu.y\"\n   796→      @close=\"closeCtxMenu\"\n   797→      @renamed=\"onPackRenamed\"\n   798→      @duplicated=\"onPackDuplicated\"\n   799→      @deleted=\"onPackDeleted\"\n   800→    />\n   801→  </Teleport>\n   802→</template>\n   803→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cac4cc3a-a489-4a33-8e33-38a50ff4c60b","uuid":"91741f5a-2183-49ff-b953-e888e037b3d6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/worktrees/sound-packs-patchbay/src/components/SoundsDialog.vue","content":"<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nimport {\n  ref,\n  computed,\n  watch,\n  nextTick,\n  onMounted,\n  onUnmounted,\n} from 'vue';\nimport { listen } from '@tauri-apps/api/event';\nimport type { UnlistenFn } from '@tauri-apps/api/event';\nimport { open } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';\nimport {\n  mkdir,\n  readFile,\n  writeFile,\n  exists,\n} from '@tauri-apps/plugin-fs';\nimport JSZip from 'jszip';\nimport { useSoundStore, AGENT_EVENT_TYPES } from '../stores/soundStore';\nimport type { PackManifestSound } from '../stores/soundStore';\nimport type { AgentEvent, AgentEventType } from '../drivers/types';\nimport PackContextMenu from './PackContextMenu.vue';\n\nconst emit = defineEmits<{ close: [] }>();\n\nconst soundStore = useSoundStore();\n\n// ---- Global settings ----\nconst globalEnabled = computed({\n  get: () => soundStore.config.enabled,\n  set: (v: boolean) => { soundStore.config.enabled = v; void soundStore.saveConfig(); },\n});\nconst globalVolume = computed({\n  get: () => Math.round(soundStore.config.globalVolume * 100),\n  set: (v: number) => { soundStore.config.globalVolume = v / 100; void soundStore.saveConfig(); },\n});\nconst cooldown = computed({\n  get: () => soundStore.config.cooldownSeconds,\n  set: (v: number) => { soundStore.config.cooldownSeconds = v; void soundStore.saveConfig(); },\n});\n\n// ---- Pack list ----\nconst selectedPack = ref<string | null>(null);\nconst rightPanel = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);\n\nonMounted(async () => {\n  await soundStore.init();\n  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n  if (soundStore.packs.length > 0 && soundStore.packs[0]) {\n    selectedPack.value = soundStore.packs[0].name;\n  }\n  agentEventUnlisten = await listen<string>(\n    'agent-event',\n    (e) => {\n      try {\n        const parsed = JSON.parse(e.payload) as AgentEvent;\n        flashEventRow(parsed.type);\n      } catch { /* ignore parse errors */ }\n    },\n  );\n});\n\nonUnmounted(() => {\n  if (agentEventUnlisten) agentEventUnlisten();\n  if (flashTimeout) clearTimeout(flashTimeout);\n});\n\nfunction isPackActive(packName: string): boolean {\n  return soundStore.config.activePacks.includes(packName);\n}\n\nfunction togglePackActive(packName: string, active: boolean) {\n  if (active) {\n    if (!soundStore.config.activePacks.includes(packName)) {\n      soundStore.config.activePacks.push(packName);\n    }\n  } else {\n    soundStore.config.activePacks = soundStore.config.activePacks.filter(\n      (p) => p !== packName,\n    );\n  }\n  void soundStore.saveConfig();\n}\n\nfunction selectPack(name: string) {\n  selectedPack.value = name;\n  void nextTick(() => {\n    if (rightPanel.value) rightPanel.value.scrollTop = 0;\n  });\n}\n\n// ---- Context menu ----\nconst ctxMenu = ref<{ packName: string; x: number; y: number } | null>(null);\n\nfunction onPackRightClick(e: MouseEvent, packName: string) {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  ctxMenu.value = { packName, x: e.clientX, y: e.clientY };\n}\n\nfunction closeCtxMenu() {\n  ctxMenu.value = null;\n}\n\nasync function onPackRenamed(oldName: string, newName: string) {\n  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n  if (selectedPack.value === oldName) selectedPack.value = newName;\n  closeCtxMenu();\n}\n\nasync function onPackDuplicated() {\n  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n  closeCtxMenu();\n}\n\nasync function onPackDeleted(name: string) {\n  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n  if (selectedPack.value === name) {\n    selectedPack.value = soundStore.packs[0]?.name ?? null;\n  }\n  closeCtxMenu();\n}\n\n// ---- New pack ----\nconst newPackName = ref('');\nconst creatingPack = ref(false);\nconst newPackInput = ref<HTMLInputElement | null>(null);\n\nfunction startCreatePack() {\n  creatingPack.value = true;\n  newPackName.value = '';\n  void nextTick(() => newPackInput.value?.focus());\n}\n\nfunction cancelCreatePack() {\n  creatingPack.value = false;\n  newPackName.value = '';\n}\n\nasync function confirmCreatePack() {\n  const packName = newPackName.value.trim();\n  if (!packName) return;\n  creatingPack.value = false;\n  newPackName.value = '';\n  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n  const packPath = `${baseDir}/${packName}`;\n  try {\n    await mkdir(packPath, { recursive: true });\n    for (const eventType of AGENT_EVENT_TYPES) {\n      await mkdir(`${packPath}/${eventType}`, { recursive: true });\n    }\n    await soundStore.scanPacks();\n    selectedPack.value = packName;\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error('[SoundsDialog] createNewPack failed', err);\n  }\n}\n\n// ---- Import zip ----\nconst dragOver = ref(false);\n\nasync function importZipBytes(filename: string, bytes: Uint8Array): Promise<void> {\n  const dotIdx = filename.lastIndexOf('.');\n  const packName = dotIdx > 0 ? filename.slice(0, dotIdx) : filename;\n  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n  const packPath = `${baseDir}/${packName}`;\n\n  const zip = await JSZip.loadAsync(bytes);\n  for (const [relativePath, file] of Object.entries(zip.files)) {\n    if (file.dir) {\n      await mkdir(`${packPath}/${relativePath}`, { recursive: true });\n    } else {\n      const data = await file.async('uint8array');\n      const dirPart = relativePath.includes('/')\n        ? relativePath.slice(0, relativePath.lastIndexOf('/'))\n        : '';\n      if (dirPart) {\n        await mkdir(`${packPath}/${dirPart}`, { recursive: true });\n      }\n      await writeFile(`${packPath}/${relativePath}`, data);\n    }\n  }\n\n  await soundStore.scanPacks();\n  selectedPack.value = packName;\n}\n\nasync function openImportPicker() {\n  const result = await open({\n    filters: [{ name: 'ZIP', extensions: ['zip'] }],\n    multiple: false,\n  });\n  if (!result) return;\n  const filePath = typeof result === 'string' ? result : result;\n  if (!filePath) return;\n  try {\n    const bytes = await readFile(filePath);\n    const filename = (filePath as string).split('/').pop() ?? 'pack.zip';\n    await importZipBytes(filename, bytes);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error('[SoundsDialog] import failed', err);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction onDragOver(e: DragEvent) {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  dragOver.value = true;\n}\n\nfunction onDragLeave() {\n  dragOver.value = false;\n}\n\nasync function onDrop(e: DragEvent) {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  dragOver.value = false;\n  const file = e.dataTransfer?.files[0];\n  if (!file) return;\n  try {\n    const arrayBuffer = await file.arrayBuffer();\n    await importZipBytes(file.name, new Uint8Array(arrayBuffer));\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error('[SoundsDialog] drop import failed', err);\n  }\n}\n\n// ---- Event descriptions ----\nconst EVENT_DESCRIPTIONS: Record<string, string> = {\n  session_start: 'Agent session begins.',\n  session_end: 'Agent session ends or is interrupted.',\n  prompt_submit: 'User submits a prompt to the agent.',\n  tool_start: 'Agent begins executing a tool (e.g. Bash, Read, Edit).',\n  tool_end: 'Agent finishes executing a tool.',\n  turn_end: 'Agent completes a full response turn.',\n  permission_wait: 'Agent pauses waiting for the user to approve a tool call.',\n  subagent_start: 'A subagent is spawned by the parent agent.',\n  subagent_end: 'A subagent finishes its work.',\n  idle_notification: 'Agent has been idle and sends a nudge notification.',\n  elicitation_wait: 'Agent pauses waiting for user input.',\n  auth_success: 'Authentication to an external service succeeds.',\n  worktree_create: 'A new git worktree is created.',\n  worktree_remove: 'A git worktree is removed.',\n  teammate_idle: \"A teammate's agent session goes idle.\",\n  task_completed: 'Agent marks a task as completed.',\n};\n\nconst activeInfoPopover = ref<string | null>(null);\n\nfunction toggleInfoPopover(eventType: string) {\n  activeInfoPopover.value = activeInfoPopover.value === eventType ? null : eventType;\n}\n\n// ---- Patchbay data ----\nconst selectedPackInfo = computed(() =>\n  soundStore.packs.find((p) => p.name === selectedPack.value) ?? null,\n);\n\nfunction hasAssignments(eventType: AgentEventType): boolean {\n  if (!selectedPackInfo.value) return false;\n  return selectedPackInfo.value.manifest.assignments.some((a) => a.event === eventType);\n}\n\n// ---- Sound preview (left column) ----\nlet previewSource: AudioBufferSourceNode | null = null;\nconst previewFile = ref<string | null>(null);\nconst soundFileExists = ref<Map<string, boolean>>(new Map());\nconst hoveredSoundFile = ref<string | null>(null);\n\nasync function checkSoundFileExistence(packName: string): Promise<void> {\n  const sounds = selectedPackInfo.value?.manifest.sounds ?? [];\n  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n  const newMap = new Map<string, boolean>();\n  await Promise.all(\n    sounds.map(async (sound) => {\n      const filePath = `${baseDir}/${packName}/${sound.file}`;\n      const fileExists = await exists(filePath);\n      newMap.set(sound.file, fileExists);\n    }),\n  );\n  soundFileExists.value = newMap;\n}\n\nfunction stopPreview(): void {\n  if (previewSource) {\n    try { previewSource.stop(); } catch { /* already stopped */ }\n    previewSource = null;\n  }\n  previewFile.value = null;\n}\n\nasync function playPreview(filename: string): Promise<void> {\n  if (!selectedPack.value) return;\n  stopPreview();\n  const baseDir = soundStore.getSoundPacksDir();\n  const filePath = `${baseDir}/${selectedPack.value}/${filename}`;\n  const buffer = await soundStore.loadBuffer(filePath);\n  if (!buffer) return;\n  const ctx = soundStore.getOrCreateAudioContext();\n  const sound = selectedPackInfo.value?.manifest.sounds.find((s) => s.file === filename);\n  const gainNode = ctx.createGain();\n  gainNode.gain.value =\n    soundStore.config.globalVolume * soundStore.effectiveVolume(selectedPack.value, filename, sound);\n  gainNode.connect(ctx.destination);\n  const source = ctx.createBufferSource();\n  source.buffer = buffer;\n  source.connect(gainNode);\n  previewFile.value = filename;\n  previewSource = source;\n  source.onended = () => {\n    if (previewFile.value === filename) {\n      previewFile.value = null;\n      previewSource = null;\n    }\n  };\n  source.start();\n}\n\nasync function updateSoundVolume(sound: PackManifestSound, volume: number): Promise<void> {\n  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n  sound.volume = volume;\n  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, selectedPackInfo.value.manifest);\n}\n\nasync function updateSoundEnabled(sound: PackManifestSound, enabled: boolean): Promise<void> {\n  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n  sound.enabled = enabled;\n  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, selectedPackInfo.value.manifest);\n}\n\n// ---- Assignment chips (right column) ----\nfunction assignmentsForEvent(eventType: AgentEventType): string[] {\n  if (!selectedPackInfo.value) return [];\n  return selectedPackInfo.value.manifest.assignments\n    .filter((a) => a.event === eventType)\n    .map((a) => a.file);\n}\n\nfunction truncateFilename(name: string, max = 20): string {\n  if (name.length <= max) return name;\n  return name.slice(0, max - 1) + '\\u2026';\n}\n\nasync function removeAssignment(\n  file: string,\n  eventType: AgentEventType,\n): Promise<void> {\n  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n  const manifest = selectedPackInfo.value.manifest;\n  manifest.assignments = manifest.assignments.filter(\n    (a) => !(a.file === file && a.event === eventType),\n  );\n  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, manifest);\n}\n\n// ---- Drag-and-drop: sound → event row ----\nconst draggingSoundFile = ref<string | null>(null);\nconst dragOverEventType = ref<AgentEventType | null>(null);\n\n// ---- Drag-and-drop: chip → sound row (re-assign) ----\nconst draggingChip = ref<{ file: string; event: AgentEventType } | null>(null);\nconst dragOverSoundFile = ref<string | null>(null);\n\nfunction onSoundDragStart(e: DragEvent, filename: string): void {\n  draggingSoundFile.value = filename;\n  if (e.dataTransfer) {\n    e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = 'copy';\n    e.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', filename);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction onSoundDragEnd(): void {\n  draggingSoundFile.value = null;\n  dragOverEventType.value = null;\n}\n\nfunction onEventDragOver(e: DragEvent, eventType: AgentEventType): void {\n  if (!draggingSoundFile.value) return;\n  e.preventDefault();\n  if (e.dataTransfer) e.dataTransfer.dropEffect = 'copy';\n  dragOverEventType.value = eventType;\n}\n\nfunction onEventDragLeaveRow(): void {\n  dragOverEventType.value = null;\n}\n\nasync function onEventDrop(\n  e: DragEvent,\n  eventType: AgentEventType,\n): Promise<void> {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  dragOverEventType.value = null;\n  const file = draggingSoundFile.value;\n  draggingSoundFile.value = null;\n  if (!file) return;\n  await addAssignment(file, eventType);\n}\n\nasync function addAssignment(\n  file: string,\n  eventType: AgentEventType,\n): Promise<void> {\n  if (!selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n  const manifest = selectedPackInfo.value.manifest;\n  const alreadyExists = manifest.assignments.some(\n    (a) => a.file === file && a.event === eventType,\n  );\n  if (alreadyExists) return;\n  manifest.assignments.push({ file, event: eventType });\n  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, manifest);\n}\n\n// ---- Chip drag handlers (re-assign chip to different sound) ----\nfunction onChipDragStart(\n  e: DragEvent,\n  file: string,\n  eventType: AgentEventType,\n): void {\n  draggingChip.value = { file, event: eventType };\n  if (e.dataTransfer) {\n    e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = 'move';\n    e.dataTransfer.setData('text/plain', file);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction onChipDragEnd(): void {\n  draggingChip.value = null;\n  dragOverSoundFile.value = null;\n}\n\nfunction onSoundRowDragOver(e: DragEvent, filename: string): void {\n  if (!draggingChip.value) return;\n  e.preventDefault();\n  if (e.dataTransfer) e.dataTransfer.dropEffect = 'move';\n  dragOverSoundFile.value = filename;\n}\n\nfunction onSoundRowDragLeave(): void {\n  dragOverSoundFile.value = null;\n}\n\nasync function onSoundRowDrop(\n  e: DragEvent,\n  newFile: string,\n): Promise<void> {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  dragOverSoundFile.value = null;\n  const chip = draggingChip.value;\n  draggingChip.value = null;\n  if (!chip || !selectedPack.value || !selectedPackInfo.value) return;\n  if (chip.file === newFile) return;\n  const manifest = selectedPackInfo.value.manifest;\n  manifest.assignments = manifest.assignments.filter(\n    (a) => !(a.file === chip.file && a.event === chip.event),\n  );\n  const alreadyExists = manifest.assignments.some(\n    (a) => a.file === newFile && a.event === chip.event,\n  );\n  if (!alreadyExists) {\n    manifest.assignments.push({ file: newFile, event: chip.event });\n  }\n  await soundStore.savePackManifest(selectedPack.value, manifest);\n}\n\n// ---- Live highlight on incoming agent events ----\nconst flashingEvent = ref<AgentEventType | null>(null);\nlet flashTimeout: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null;\nlet agentEventUnlisten: UnlistenFn | null = null;\n\nfunction flashEventRow(eventType: AgentEventType): void {\n  flashingEvent.value = eventType;\n  if (flashTimeout) clearTimeout(flashTimeout);\n  flashTimeout = setTimeout(() => {\n    flashingEvent.value = null;\n    flashTimeout = null;\n  }, 200);\n}\n\n// Reset scroll + stop preview + check file existence on pack change\nwatch(selectedPack, async (packName) => {\n  stopPreview();\n  soundFileExists.value = new Map();\n  if (packName) void checkSoundFileExistence(packName);\n  await nextTick(() => {\n    if (rightPanel.value) rightPanel.value.scrollTop = 0;\n  });\n});\n\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <Teleport to=\"body\">\n    <!-- Backdrop -->\n    <div class=\"fixed inset-0 z-[100] flex items-center justify-center bg-black/50\">\n      <!-- Drop zone wrapper -->\n      <div\n        class=\"relative w-[960px] max-w-[90vw] h-[700px] max-h-[90vh] flex flex-col bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden\"\n        @dragover=\"onDragOver\"\n        @dragleave=\"onDragLeave\"\n        @drop=\"onDrop\"\n      >\n        <!-- Drag overlay -->\n        <div\n          v-if=\"dragOver\"\n          class=\"absolute inset-0 z-[150] flex items-center justify-center bg-indigo-900/80 border-2 border-dashed border-indigo-400 rounded-lg pointer-events-none\"\n        >\n          <span class=\"text-indigo-200 text-lg font-semibold\">Drop sound pack here</span>\n        </div>\n\n        <!-- Header -->\n        <div class=\"flex items-center gap-4 px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n          <span class=\"text-gray-200 font-semibold text-sm\">Sounds</span>\n\n          <!-- Master enable -->\n          <label class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-300 cursor-pointer\">\n            <input\n              type=\"checkbox\"\n              :checked=\"globalEnabled\"\n              class=\"w-4 h-4 accent-indigo-400\"\n              @change=\"globalEnabled = ($event.target as HTMLInputElement).checked\"\n            />\n            Enable\n          </label>\n\n          <!-- Global volume -->\n          <label class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-300\">\n            Vol\n            <input\n              type=\"range\"\n              min=\"0\"\n              max=\"100\"\n              :value=\"globalVolume\"\n              class=\"w-24 accent-indigo-400\"\n              @input=\"globalVolume = parseInt(($event.target as HTMLInputElement).value)\"\n            />\n            <span class=\"w-7 tabular-nums\">{{ globalVolume }}%</span>\n          </label>\n\n          <!-- Cooldown -->\n          <label class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-300\">\n            Cooldown\n            <input\n              type=\"range\"\n              min=\"0\"\n              max=\"10\"\n              step=\"0.5\"\n              :value=\"cooldown\"\n              class=\"w-20 accent-indigo-400\"\n              @input=\"cooldown = parseFloat(($event.target as HTMLInputElement).value)\"\n            />\n            <span class=\"w-8 tabular-nums\">{{ cooldown }}s</span>\n          </label>\n        </div>\n\n        <!-- Body -->\n        <div class=\"flex flex-1 min-h-0\">\n          <!-- Left panel: pack list -->\n          <div class=\"w-60 shrink-0 border-r border-gray-700 flex flex-col\">\n            <div class=\"px-3 pt-2 pb-1 text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide\">\n              Packs\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto\">\n              <div\n                v-for=\"pack in soundStore.packs\"\n                :key=\"pack.name\"\n                class=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-2 py-1.5 cursor-pointer rounded mx-1\"\n                :class=\"selectedPack === pack.name ? 'bg-gray-700' : 'hover:bg-gray-800'\"\n                @click=\"selectPack(pack.name)\"\n                @contextmenu=\"onPackRightClick($event, pack.name)\"\n              >\n                <input\n                  type=\"checkbox\"\n                  :checked=\"isPackActive(pack.name)\"\n                  class=\"w-4 h-4 accent-indigo-400 cursor-pointer\"\n                  @click.stop\n                  @change=\"togglePackActive(pack.name, ($event.target as HTMLInputElement).checked)\"\n                />\n                <span class=\"text-sm text-gray-200 truncate flex-1\">{{ pack.name }}</span>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            <!-- Buttons / new pack input -->\n            <div class=\"flex flex-col gap-1 p-2 border-t border-gray-700\">\n              <div v-if=\"creatingPack\" class=\"flex gap-1\">\n                <input\n                  ref=\"newPackInput\"\n                  v-model=\"newPackName\"\n                  class=\"flex-1 px-2 py-1 bg-gray-800 border border-gray-600 rounded text-xs text-gray-200 outline-none focus:border-indigo-400\"\n                  placeholder=\"Pack name…\"\n                  @keydown.enter=\"confirmCreatePack\"\n                  @keydown.escape=\"cancelCreatePack\"\n                />\n                <button\n                  class=\"px-2 py-1 bg-indigo-600/80 rounded hover:bg-indigo-500 text-xs text-white\"\n                  @click=\"confirmCreatePack\"\n                >OK</button>\n              </div>\n              <div class=\"flex gap-1\">\n                <button\n                  class=\"flex-1 px-2 py-1 bg-gray-700/60 rounded hover:bg-gray-600/70 text-xs text-gray-200\"\n                  @click=\"startCreatePack\"\n                >\n                  New Pack\n                </button>\n                <button\n                  class=\"flex-1 px-2 py-1 bg-gray-700/60 rounded hover:bg-gray-600/70 text-xs text-gray-200\"\n                  @click=\"openImportPicker\"\n                >\n                  Import\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n\n          <!-- Patchbay: Sounds + Events columns -->\n          <div ref=\"rightPanel\" class=\"flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden\">\n            <!-- Sounds column -->\n            <div class=\"flex-1 border-r border-gray-700 flex flex-col min-w-0\">\n              <div class=\"px-3 py-2 border-b border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n                <span class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide\">Sounds</span>\n              </div>\n              <div class=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto\">\n                <div\n                  v-if=\"!selectedPackInfo\"\n                  class=\"flex items-center justify-center h-full text-gray-600 text-sm\"\n                >\n                  Select a pack\n                </div>\n                <div\n                  v-else-if=\"selectedPackInfo.manifest.sounds.length === 0\"\n                  class=\"flex items-center justify-center h-full text-gray-600 text-sm\"\n                >\n                  No sounds in this pack\n                </div>\n                <div\n                  v-for=\"sound in selectedPackInfo.manifest.sounds\"\n                  v-else\n                  :key=\"sound.file\"\n                  draggable=\"true\"\n                  class=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 border-b border-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-800/40 cursor-grab transition-colors duration-150\"\n                  :class=\"[\n                    draggingSoundFile === sound.file ? 'opacity-50' : '',\n                    dragOverSoundFile === sound.file ? 'bg-indigo-500/20' : '',\n                    draggingChip ? 'opacity-100' : '',\n                  ]\"\n                  @mouseenter=\"hoveredSoundFile = sound.file\"\n                  @mouseleave=\"hoveredSoundFile = null\"\n                  @dragstart=\"onSoundDragStart($event, sound.file)\"\n                  @dragend=\"onSoundDragEnd\"\n                  @dragover=\"onSoundRowDragOver($event, sound.file)\"\n                  @dragleave=\"onSoundRowDragLeave\"\n                  @drop=\"onSoundRowDrop($event, sound.file)\"\n                >\n                  <!-- Play button -->\n                  <button\n                    class=\"shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded text-gray-400 hover:text-white hover:bg-gray-700 text-xs\"\n                    title=\"Play preview\"\n                    @click=\"playPreview(sound.file)\"\n                  >▶</button>\n\n                  <!-- Filename -->\n                  <span class=\"flex-1 text-xs font-mono text-gray-200 truncate min-w-0\">{{ sound.file }}</span>\n\n                  <!-- Broken link indicator -->\n                  <span\n                    v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(sound.file) === false\"\n                    class=\"shrink-0 text-red-400 text-xs\"\n                    title=\"File not found on disk\"\n                  >⚠</span>\n\n                  <!-- Volume slider (visible on hover) -->\n                  <input\n                    v-show=\"hoveredSoundFile === sound.file\"\n                    type=\"range\"\n                    min=\"0\"\n                    max=\"1\"\n                    step=\"0.01\"\n                    :value=\"sound.volume\"\n                    class=\"shrink-0 w-16 accent-indigo-400\"\n                    title=\"Volume\"\n                    @input=\"updateSoundVolume(sound, parseFloat(($event.target as HTMLInputElement).value))\"\n                  />\n\n                  <!-- Enabled toggle -->\n                  <input\n                    type=\"checkbox\"\n                    :checked=\"sound.enabled\"\n                    class=\"shrink-0 w-4 h-4 accent-indigo-400 cursor-pointer\"\n                    title=\"Enable/disable this sound\"\n                    @change=\"updateSoundEnabled(sound, ($event.target as HTMLInputElement).checked)\"\n                  />\n\n                  <!-- Stop button -->\n                  <button\n                    class=\"shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded text-xs\"\n                    :class=\"previewFile === sound.file\n                      ? 'text-red-400 hover:text-red-300 hover:bg-gray-700'\n                      : 'text-gray-600 cursor-default'\"\n                    title=\"Stop preview\"\n                    @click=\"previewFile === sound.file ? stopPreview() : undefined\"\n                  >■</button>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n\n            <!-- Events column -->\n            <div class=\"flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0\">\n              <div class=\"px-3 py-2 border-b border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n                <span class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide\">Events</span>\n              </div>\n              <div class=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto\">\n                <div\n                  v-for=\"eventType in AGENT_EVENT_TYPES\"\n                  :key=\"eventType\"\n                  class=\"px-3 py-2 border-b border-gray-800 transition-all duration-200\"\n                  :class=\"[\n                    hasAssignments(eventType) ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-40',\n                    flashingEvent === eventType ? 'bg-indigo-600/30' : '',\n                    dragOverEventType === eventType ? 'bg-indigo-500/20 opacity-100' : '',\n                    draggingSoundFile ? 'opacity-100' : '',\n                  ]\"\n                  @dragover=\"onEventDragOver($event, eventType)\"\n                  @dragleave=\"onEventDragLeaveRow\"\n                  @drop=\"onEventDrop($event, eventType)\"\n                >\n                  <div class=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n                    <span class=\"text-sm font-mono text-gray-300 flex-1\">{{ eventType }}</span>\n                    <!-- Info icon + popover -->\n                    <span\n                      v-if=\"EVENT_DESCRIPTIONS[eventType]\"\n                      class=\"relative shrink-0\"\n                      @click.stop\n                    >\n                      <span\n                        class=\"w-4 h-4 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border text-[10px] leading-none cursor-pointer select-none\"\n                        :class=\"activeInfoPopover === eventType\n                          ? 'border-indigo-400 text-indigo-300 bg-indigo-900/40'\n                          : 'border-gray-500 text-gray-400 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-200'\"\n                        @click=\"toggleInfoPopover(eventType)\"\n                      >i</span>\n                      <div\n                        v-if=\"activeInfoPopover === eventType\"\n                        class=\"absolute right-0 top-6 z-50 w-56 bg-gray-800 border border-gray-600 rounded shadow-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs text-gray-200 leading-relaxed\"\n                      >\n                        {{ EVENT_DESCRIPTIONS[eventType] }}\n                      </div>\n                    </span>\n                  </div>\n                  <!-- Assignment chips -->\n                  <div\n                    v-if=\"assignmentsForEvent(eventType).length > 0\"\n                    class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-1 mt-1\"\n                  >\n                    <span\n                      v-for=\"file in assignmentsForEvent(eventType)\"\n                      :key=\"file\"\n                      draggable=\"true\"\n                      class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 bg-gray-700/80 rounded text-xs text-gray-200 cursor-grab hover:bg-gray-600/80\"\n                      :class=\"draggingChip?.file === file && draggingChip?.event === eventType ? 'opacity-50' : ''\"\n                      :title=\"file\"\n                      @click=\"playPreview(file)\"\n                      @dragstart.stop=\"onChipDragStart($event, file, eventType)\"\n                      @dragend=\"onChipDragEnd\"\n                    >\n                      {{ truncateFilename(file) }}\n                      <button\n                        class=\"ml-0.5 text-gray-400 hover:text-red-400 leading-none\"\n                        title=\"Remove assignment\"\n                        @click.stop=\"removeAssignment(file, eventType)\"\n                      >&times;</button>\n                    </span>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <!-- Footer -->\n        <div class=\"flex justify-end px-4 py-3 border-t border-gray-700 shrink-0\">\n          <button\n            class=\"px-4 py-1.5 bg-gray-700/60 rounded hover:bg-gray-600/70 text-sm text-gray-200\"\n            @click=\"emit('close')\"\n          >\n            Close\n          </button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Context menu -->\n    <PackContextMenu\n      v-if=\"ctxMenu\"\n      :pack-name=\"ctxMenu.packName\"\n      :x=\"ctxMenu.x\"\n      :y=\"ctxMenu.y\"\n      @close=\"closeCtxMenu\"\n      @renamed=\"onPackRenamed\"\n      @duplicated=\"onPackDuplicated\"\n      @deleted=\"onPackDeleted\"\n    />\n  </Teleport>\n</template>\n","numLines":803,"startLine":1,"totalLines":803}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01T7MsdNPGRN9SRhw7v8q3fT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01C5u5WuA8WjnuFeE5bfG7ne","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/worktrees/sound-packs-patchbay/src/stores/soundStore.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6201,"cache_read_input_tokens":37498,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6201},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cac4cc3a-a489-4a33-8e33-38a50ff4c60b","uuid":"8961bdcf-7c9f-42f6-94cf-462356ebb12e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C5u5WuA8WjnuFeE5bfG7ne","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { defineStore } from 'pinia';\n     2→import { ref } from 'vue';\n     3→import { homeDir } from '@tauri-apps/api/path';\n     4→import {\n     5→  readTextFile,\n     6→  writeTextFile,\n     7→  mkdir,\n     8→  exists,\n     9→  readDir,\n    10→  readFile,\n    11→} from '@tauri-apps/plugin-fs';\n    12→import type { AgentEvent, AgentEventType } from '../drivers/types';\n    13→\n    14→export const AGENT_EVENT_TYPES: AgentEventType[] = [\n    15→  'session_start',\n    16→  'session_end',\n    17→  'prompt_submit',\n    18→  'tool_start',\n    19→  'tool_end',\n    20→  'turn_end',\n    21→  'permission_wait',\n    22→  'subagent_start',\n    23→  'subagent_end',\n    24→  'idle_notification',\n    25→  'elicitation_wait',\n    26→  'auth_success',\n    27→  'worktree_create',\n    28→  'worktree_remove',\n    29→  'teammate_idle',\n    30→  'task_completed',\n    31→];\n    32→\n    33→export interface TrackConfig {\n    34→  enabled: boolean;\n    35→  volume: number;\n    36→}\n    37→\n    38→export interface SoundConfig {\n    39→  enabled: boolean;\n    40→  globalVolume: number;\n    41→  cooldownSeconds: number;\n    42→  activePacks: string[];\n    43→  /** Per-sound overrides, key: \"<packName>/<filename>\" */\n    44→  soundOverrides: Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }>;\n    45→  /** Legacy field — read for migration only, not written on save */\n    46→  tracks?: Record<string, Record<string, TrackConfig>>;\n    47→}\n    48→\n    49→export interface PackManifestSound {\n    50→  file: string;\n    51→  volume: number;\n    52→  enabled: boolean;\n    53→}\n    54→\n    55→export interface PackManifestAssignment {\n    56→  file: string;\n    57→  event: AgentEventType;\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→export interface PackManifest {\n    61→  sounds: PackManifestSound[];\n    62→  assignments: PackManifestAssignment[];\n    63→}\n    64→\n    65→export interface PackInfo {\n    66→  name: string;\n    67→  categories: Record<string, string[]>;\n    68→  manifest: PackManifest;\n    69→  hasManifest: boolean;\n    70→}\n    71→\n    72→\n    73→const DEFAULT_CONFIG: SoundConfig = {\n    74→  enabled: true,\n    75→  globalVolume: 0.8,\n    76→  cooldownSeconds: 2,\n    77→  activePacks: [],\n    78→  soundOverrides: {},\n    79→};\n    80→\n    81→function migrateTracksToSoundOverrides(\n    82→  tracks: Record<string, Record<string, TrackConfig>>,\n    83→): Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }> {\n    84→  const overrides: Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }> = {};\n    85→  for (const [packName, packTracks] of Object.entries(tracks)) {\n    86→    for (const [categoryAndFile, trackCfg] of Object.entries(packTracks)) {\n    87→      const slashIdx = categoryAndFile.indexOf('/');\n    88→      const filename = slashIdx >= 0 ? categoryAndFile.slice(slashIdx + 1) : categoryAndFile;\n    89→      const overrideKey = `${packName}/${filename}`;\n    90→      if (!(overrideKey in overrides)) {\n    91→        overrides[overrideKey] = { volume: trackCfg.volume, enabled: trackCfg.enabled };\n    92→      }\n    93→    }\n    94→  }\n    95→  return overrides;\n    96→}\n    97→\n    98→const AUDIO_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.mp3', '.ogg', '.wav', '.flac', '.m4a', '.webm']);\n    99→\n   100→function hasAudioExtension(filename: string): boolean {\n   101→  const dot = filename.lastIndexOf('.');\n   102→  if (dot < 0) return false;\n   103→  return AUDIO_EXTENSIONS.has(filename.slice(dot).toLowerCase());\n   104→}\n   105→\n   106→export const useSoundStore = defineStore('sound', () => {\n   107→  const config = ref<SoundConfig>({ ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, soundOverrides: {} });\n   108→  const packs = ref<PackInfo[]>([]);\n   109→\n   110→  // Reactive state for sound indicator (US-009)\n   111→  const lastPlayedSessionId = ref<string | null>(null);\n   112→\n   113→  let soundPacksDir = '';\n   114→  let configPath = '';\n   115→\n   116→  // AudioContext — lazy init on first playback\n   117→  let audioCtx: AudioContext | null = null;\n   118→\n   119→  // Buffer cache: absolute file path → AudioBuffer\n   120→  const bufferCache = new Map<string, AudioBuffer>();\n   121→\n   122→  // Per-category cooldown timestamps (category → last played ms)\n   123→  const cooldownMap = new Map<string, number>();\n   124→\n   125→  // Whether any sound is currently playing\n   126→  let playing = false;\n   127→\n   128→  // Per-session pack assignment\n   129→  const sessionPacks = new Map<string, string>();\n   130→\n   131→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   132→  // Init / persistence\n   133→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   134→\n   135→  async function init(): Promise<void> {\n   136→    const home = await homeDir();\n   137→    soundPacksDir = `${home}/.agents-in-the-office/sound-packs`;\n   138→    configPath = `${soundPacksDir}/config.json`;\n   139→\n   140→    const dirExists = await exists(soundPacksDir);\n   141→    if (!dirExists) {\n   142→      await mkdir(soundPacksDir, { recursive: true });\n   143→    }\n   144→\n   145→    const cfgExists = await exists(configPath);\n   146→    if (cfgExists) {\n   147→      try {\n   148→        const raw = await readTextFile(configPath);\n   149→        const parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as Partial<SoundConfig>;\n   150→        // Migrate legacy tracks field to soundOverrides\n   151→        if (!parsed.soundOverrides && parsed.tracks) {\n   152→          parsed.soundOverrides = migrateTracksToSoundOverrides(parsed.tracks);\n   153→        }\n   154→        const { tracks: _tracks, ...rest } = parsed;\n   155→        void _tracks; // consumed by migration above, drop from config\n   156→        config.value = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, ...rest };\n   157→      } catch {\n   158→        config.value = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, soundOverrides: {} };\n   159→      }\n   160→    } else {\n   161→      config.value = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, soundOverrides: {} };\n   162→      await saveConfig();\n   163→    }\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  async function saveConfig(): Promise<void> {\n   167→    await writeTextFile(configPath, JSON.stringify(config.value, null, 2));\n   168→  }\n   169→\n   170→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   171→  // Pack manifest read/write\n   172→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   173→\n   174→  async function loadPackManifest(packName: string): Promise<PackManifest> {\n   175→    const manifestPath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}/manifest.json`;\n   176→    const manifestExists = await exists(manifestPath);\n   177→    if (!manifestExists) return { sounds: [], assignments: [] };\n   178→    try {\n   179→      const raw = await readTextFile(manifestPath);\n   180→      const parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as Partial<PackManifest>;\n   181→      return {\n   182→        sounds: Array.isArray(parsed.sounds) ? parsed.sounds : [],\n   183→        assignments: Array.isArray(parsed.assignments) ? parsed.assignments : [],\n   184→      };\n   185→    } catch {\n   186→      return { sounds: [], assignments: [] };\n   187→    }\n   188→  }\n   189→\n   190→  async function savePackManifest(packName: string, manifest: PackManifest): Promise<void> {\n   191→    const manifestPath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}/manifest.json`;\n   192→    await writeTextFile(manifestPath, JSON.stringify(manifest, null, 2));\n   193→  }\n   194→\n   195→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   196→  // Pack scanning\n   197→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   198→\n   199→  async function scanPacks(): Promise<PackInfo[]> {\n   200→    const discovered: PackInfo[] = [];\n   201→\n   202→    const dirExists = await exists(soundPacksDir);\n   203→    if (!dirExists) return discovered;\n   204→\n   205→    const entries = await readDir(soundPacksDir);\n   206→    for (const entry of entries) {\n   207→      if (!entry.isDirectory) continue;\n   208→      if (entry.name === undefined || entry.name.startsWith('.')) continue;\n   209→      const packName = entry.name;\n   210→      const packPath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}`;\n   211→      const categories: Record<string, string[]> = {};\n   212→\n   213→      const manifest = await loadPackManifest(packName);\n   214→      const hasManifest = await exists(`${packPath}/manifest.json`);\n   215→\n   216→      const catEntries = await readDir(packPath);\n   217→      for (const cat of catEntries) {\n   218→        if (!cat.isDirectory) continue;\n   219→        if (cat.name === undefined || cat.name.startsWith('.')) continue;\n   220→        const catName = cat.name;\n   221→        const catPath = `${packPath}/${catName}`;\n   222→        const fileEntries = await readDir(catPath);\n   223→        const audioFiles = fileEntries\n   224→          .filter((f) => !f.isDirectory && f.name !== undefined && hasAudioExtension(f.name))\n   225→          .map((f) => f.name as string);\n   226→        if (audioFiles.length > 0 || AGENT_EVENT_TYPES.includes(catName as AgentEventType)) {\n   227→          categories[catName] = audioFiles.sort();\n   228→        }\n   229→      }\n   230→\n   231→      for (const eventType of AGENT_EVENT_TYPES) {\n   232→        if (!(eventType in categories)) {\n   233→          categories[eventType] = [];\n   234→        }\n   235→      }\n   236→\n   237→      discovered.push({ name: packName, categories, manifest, hasManifest });\n   238→    }\n   239→\n   240→    packs.value = discovered;\n   241→    return discovered;\n   242→  }\n   243→\n   244→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   245→  // Sound override helpers (two-layer: soundOverrides → manifest default)\n   246→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   247→\n   248→  /** Extract filename from \"category/filename\" or plain \"filename\" key. */\n   249→  function extractFilename(categoryAndFile: string): string {\n   250→    const slashIdx = categoryAndFile.indexOf('/');\n   251→    return slashIdx >= 0 ? categoryAndFile.slice(slashIdx + 1) : categoryAndFile;\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  /**\n   255→   * Effective volume for a sound: soundOverrides → manifest default → 1.0\n   256→   */\n   257→  function effectiveVolume(packName: string, filename: string, manifestSound?: PackManifestSound): number {\n   258→    const override = config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`];\n   259→    if (override !== undefined) return override.volume;\n   260→    return manifestSound?.volume ?? 1.0;\n   261→  }\n   262→\n   263→  /**\n   264→   * Effective enabled state: soundOverrides → manifest default → true\n   265→   */\n   266→  function isEnabled(packName: string, filename: string, manifestSound?: PackManifestSound): boolean {\n   267→    const override = config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`];\n   268→    if (override !== undefined) return override.enabled;\n   269→    return manifestSound?.enabled ?? true;\n   270→  }\n   271→\n   272→  /**\n   273→   * Get track config for a sound. Accepts legacy \"category/filename\" key format.\n   274→   * Reads from soundOverrides using packName/filename key.\n   275→   */\n   276→  function getTrackConfig(packName: string, categoryAndFile: string): TrackConfig {\n   277→    const filename = extractFilename(categoryAndFile);\n   278→    const override = config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`];\n   279→    return override ?? { enabled: true, volume: 1.0 };\n   280→  }\n   281→\n   282→  /**\n   283→   * Set track config for a sound. Accepts legacy \"category/filename\" key format.\n   284→   * Writes to soundOverrides using packName/filename key.\n   285→   */\n   286→  function setTrackConfig(packName: string, categoryAndFile: string, track: TrackConfig): void {\n   287→    const filename = extractFilename(categoryAndFile);\n   288→    config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`] = track;\n   289→  }\n   290→\n   291→  function getSoundPacksDir(): string {\n   292→    return soundPacksDir;\n   293→  }\n   294→\n   295→  function getSessionPack(sessionId: string): string | undefined {\n   296→    return sessionPacks.get(sessionId);\n   297→  }\n   298→\n   299→  function assignSessionPack(sessionId: string, preferredPacks: string[]): void {\n   300→    const pool = preferredPacks.length > 0 ? preferredPacks : config.value.activePacks;\n   301→    if (pool.length === 0) return;\n   302→    const chosen = pool[Math.floor(Math.random() * pool.length)];\n   303→    if (chosen !== undefined) {\n   304→      sessionPacks.set(sessionId, chosen);\n   305→    }\n   306→  }\n   307→\n   308→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   309→  // AudioContext helpers\n   310→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   311→\n   312→  function getAudioContext(): AudioContext {\n   313→    if (!audioCtx) {\n   314→      audioCtx = new AudioContext();\n   315→    }\n   316→    return audioCtx;\n   317→  }\n   318→\n   319→  async function loadBuffer(filePath: string): Promise<AudioBuffer | null> {\n   320→    const cached = bufferCache.get(filePath);\n   321→    if (cached !== undefined) return cached;\n   322→\n   323→    try {\n   324→      const bytes = await readFile(filePath);\n   325→      const ctx = getAudioContext();\n   326→      const buffer = await ctx.decodeAudioData(bytes.buffer as ArrayBuffer);\n   327→      bufferCache.set(filePath, buffer);\n   328→      return buffer;\n   329→    } catch (err) {\n   330→      console.warn(`[soundStore] Failed to decode audio: ${filePath}`, err);\n   331→      return null;\n   332→    }\n   333→  }\n   334→\n   335→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   336→  // Playback engine\n   337→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   338→\n   339→  async function playForEvent(event: AgentEvent): Promise<void> {\n   340→    if (!config.value.enabled) return;\n   341→\n   342→    // Session pack assignment on session_start\n   343→    if (event.type === 'session_start') {\n   344→      const { activePacks } = config.value;\n   345→      if (activePacks.length > 0) {\n   346→        const randomIdx = Math.floor(Math.random() * activePacks.length);\n   347→        const chosen = activePacks[randomIdx];\n   348→        if (chosen !== undefined) {\n   349→          sessionPacks.set(event.sessionId, chosen);\n   350→        }\n   351→      }\n   352→    }\n   353→\n   354→    const packName = sessionPacks.get(event.sessionId);\n   355→    if (!packName) return;\n   356→\n   357→    const category = event.type;\n   358→    const now = Date.now();\n   359→    const cooldownMs = config.value.cooldownSeconds * 1000;\n   360→    const lastPlayed = cooldownMap.get(category) ?? 0;\n   361→    if (now - lastPlayed < cooldownMs) return;\n   362→\n   363→    if (playing) return;\n   364→\n   365→    // Find the pack info\n   366→    const packInfo = packs.value.find((p) => p.name === packName);\n   367→    if (!packInfo) return;\n   368→\n   369→    // Look up manifest assignments for this event type\n   370→    const assignedFiles = packInfo.manifest.assignments\n   371→      .filter((a) => a.event === event.type)\n   372→      .map((a) => a.file);\n   373→\n   374→    // Build a lookup map for manifest sound defaults\n   375→    const manifestSoundMap = new Map(packInfo.manifest.sounds.map((s) => [s.file, s]));\n   376→\n   377→    // Filter to enabled files using two-layer rule (soundOverrides → manifest default)\n   378→    const enabledFiles = assignedFiles.filter((filename) =>\n   379→      isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename)),\n   380→    );\n   381→\n   382→    if (enabledFiles.length === 0) return;\n   383→\n   384→    const randomFileIdx = Math.floor(Math.random() * enabledFiles.length);\n   385→    const chosenFile = enabledFiles[randomFileIdx];\n   386→    if (chosenFile === undefined) return;\n   387→\n   388→    // Files live at pack root, not in category subdirectories\n   389→    const filePath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}/${chosenFile}`;\n   390→\n   391→    // Skip missing file with a warning — no crash\n   392→    const fileOnDisk = await exists(filePath);\n   393→    if (!fileOnDisk) {\n   394→      console.warn(`[soundStore] Sound file not found on disk, skipping: ${filePath}`);\n   395→      return;\n   396→    }\n   397→\n   398→    const buffer = await loadBuffer(filePath);\n   399→    if (!buffer) return;\n   400→\n   401→    const manifestSound = manifestSoundMap.get(chosenFile);\n   402→    const vol = effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound);\n   403→    const ctx = getAudioContext();\n   404→\n   405→    const gainNode = ctx.createGain();\n   406→    gainNode.gain.value = config.value.globalVolume * vol;\n   407→    gainNode.connect(ctx.destination);\n   408→\n   409→    const source = ctx.createBufferSource();\n   410→    source.buffer = buffer;\n   411→    source.connect(gainNode);\n   412→\n   413→    playing = true;\n   414→    cooldownMap.set(category, now);\n   415→    lastPlayedSessionId.value = event.sessionId;\n   416→\n   417→    source.onended = () => {\n   418→      playing = false;\n   419→    };\n   420→\n   421→    source.start();\n   422→  }\n   423→\n   424→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   425→  // Public AudioContext access (for AudioPlayer.vue)\n   426→  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   427→\n   428→  function getOrCreateAudioContext(): AudioContext {\n   429→    return getAudioContext();\n   430→  }\n   431→\n   432→  function getBufferCache(): Map<string, AudioBuffer> {\n   433→    return bufferCache;\n   434→  }\n   435→\n   436→  return {\n   437→    config,\n   438→    packs,\n   439→    lastPlayedSessionId,\n   440→    init,\n   441→    saveConfig,\n   442→    scanPacks,\n   443→    loadPackManifest,\n   444→    savePackManifest,\n   445→    getTrackConfig,\n   446→    setTrackConfig,\n   447→    effectiveVolume,\n   448→    isEnabled,\n   449→    getSoundPacksDir,\n   450→    playForEvent,\n   451→    getOrCreateAudioContext,\n   452→    getBufferCache,\n   453→    loadBuffer,\n   454→    getSessionPack,\n   455→    assignSessionPack,\n   456→  };\n   457→});\n   458→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cac4cc3a-a489-4a33-8e33-38a50ff4c60b","uuid":"7403d9d8-7687-4b35-a1cb-c7fe04758215","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/worktrees/sound-packs-patchbay/src/stores/soundStore.ts","content":"import { defineStore } from 'pinia';\nimport { ref } from 'vue';\nimport { homeDir } from '@tauri-apps/api/path';\nimport {\n  readTextFile,\n  writeTextFile,\n  mkdir,\n  exists,\n  readDir,\n  readFile,\n} from '@tauri-apps/plugin-fs';\nimport type { AgentEvent, AgentEventType } from '../drivers/types';\n\nexport const AGENT_EVENT_TYPES: AgentEventType[] = [\n  'session_start',\n  'session_end',\n  'prompt_submit',\n  'tool_start',\n  'tool_end',\n  'turn_end',\n  'permission_wait',\n  'subagent_start',\n  'subagent_end',\n  'idle_notification',\n  'elicitation_wait',\n  'auth_success',\n  'worktree_create',\n  'worktree_remove',\n  'teammate_idle',\n  'task_completed',\n];\n\nexport interface TrackConfig {\n  enabled: boolean;\n  volume: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SoundConfig {\n  enabled: boolean;\n  globalVolume: number;\n  cooldownSeconds: number;\n  activePacks: string[];\n  /** Per-sound overrides, key: \"<packName>/<filename>\" */\n  soundOverrides: Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }>;\n  /** Legacy field — read for migration only, not written on save */\n  tracks?: Record<string, Record<string, TrackConfig>>;\n}\n\nexport interface PackManifestSound {\n  file: string;\n  volume: number;\n  enabled: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface PackManifestAssignment {\n  file: string;\n  event: AgentEventType;\n}\n\nexport interface PackManifest {\n  sounds: PackManifestSound[];\n  assignments: PackManifestAssignment[];\n}\n\nexport interface PackInfo {\n  name: string;\n  categories: Record<string, string[]>;\n  manifest: PackManifest;\n  hasManifest: boolean;\n}\n\n\nconst DEFAULT_CONFIG: SoundConfig = {\n  enabled: true,\n  globalVolume: 0.8,\n  cooldownSeconds: 2,\n  activePacks: [],\n  soundOverrides: {},\n};\n\nfunction migrateTracksToSoundOverrides(\n  tracks: Record<string, Record<string, TrackConfig>>,\n): Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }> {\n  const overrides: Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }> = {};\n  for (const [packName, packTracks] of Object.entries(tracks)) {\n    for (const [categoryAndFile, trackCfg] of Object.entries(packTracks)) {\n      const slashIdx = categoryAndFile.indexOf('/');\n      const filename = slashIdx >= 0 ? categoryAndFile.slice(slashIdx + 1) : categoryAndFile;\n      const overrideKey = `${packName}/${filename}`;\n      if (!(overrideKey in overrides)) {\n        overrides[overrideKey] = { volume: trackCfg.volume, enabled: trackCfg.enabled };\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return overrides;\n}\n\nconst AUDIO_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.mp3', '.ogg', '.wav', '.flac', '.m4a', '.webm']);\n\nfunction hasAudioExtension(filename: string): boolean {\n  const dot = filename.lastIndexOf('.');\n  if (dot < 0) return false;\n  return AUDIO_EXTENSIONS.has(filename.slice(dot).toLowerCase());\n}\n\nexport const useSoundStore = defineStore('sound', () => {\n  const config = ref<SoundConfig>({ ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, soundOverrides: {} });\n  const packs = ref<PackInfo[]>([]);\n\n  // Reactive state for sound indicator (US-009)\n  const lastPlayedSessionId = ref<string | null>(null);\n\n  let soundPacksDir = '';\n  let configPath = '';\n\n  // AudioContext — lazy init on first playback\n  let audioCtx: AudioContext | null = null;\n\n  // Buffer cache: absolute file path → AudioBuffer\n  const bufferCache = new Map<string, AudioBuffer>();\n\n  // Per-category cooldown timestamps (category → last played ms)\n  const cooldownMap = new Map<string, number>();\n\n  // Whether any sound is currently playing\n  let playing = false;\n\n  // Per-session pack assignment\n  const sessionPacks = new Map<string, string>();\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Init / persistence\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  async function init(): Promise<void> {\n    const home = await homeDir();\n    soundPacksDir = `${home}/.agents-in-the-office/sound-packs`;\n    configPath = `${soundPacksDir}/config.json`;\n\n    const dirExists = await exists(soundPacksDir);\n    if (!dirExists) {\n      await mkdir(soundPacksDir, { recursive: true });\n    }\n\n    const cfgExists = await exists(configPath);\n    if (cfgExists) {\n      try {\n        const raw = await readTextFile(configPath);\n        const parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as Partial<SoundConfig>;\n        // Migrate legacy tracks field to soundOverrides\n        if (!parsed.soundOverrides && parsed.tracks) {\n          parsed.soundOverrides = migrateTracksToSoundOverrides(parsed.tracks);\n        }\n        const { tracks: _tracks, ...rest } = parsed;\n        void _tracks; // consumed by migration above, drop from config\n        config.value = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, ...rest };\n      } catch {\n        config.value = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, soundOverrides: {} };\n      }\n    } else {\n      config.value = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, soundOverrides: {} };\n      await saveConfig();\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function saveConfig(): Promise<void> {\n    await writeTextFile(configPath, JSON.stringify(config.value, null, 2));\n  }\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Pack manifest read/write\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  async function loadPackManifest(packName: string): Promise<PackManifest> {\n    const manifestPath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}/manifest.json`;\n    const manifestExists = await exists(manifestPath);\n    if (!manifestExists) return { sounds: [], assignments: [] };\n    try {\n      const raw = await readTextFile(manifestPath);\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as Partial<PackManifest>;\n      return {\n        sounds: Array.isArray(parsed.sounds) ? parsed.sounds : [],\n        assignments: Array.isArray(parsed.assignments) ? parsed.assignments : [],\n      };\n    } catch {\n      return { sounds: [], assignments: [] };\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function savePackManifest(packName: string, manifest: PackManifest): Promise<void> {\n    const manifestPath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}/manifest.json`;\n    await writeTextFile(manifestPath, JSON.stringify(manifest, null, 2));\n  }\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Pack scanning\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  async function scanPacks(): Promise<PackInfo[]> {\n    const discovered: PackInfo[] = [];\n\n    const dirExists = await exists(soundPacksDir);\n    if (!dirExists) return discovered;\n\n    const entries = await readDir(soundPacksDir);\n    for (const entry of entries) {\n      if (!entry.isDirectory) continue;\n      if (entry.name === undefined || entry.name.startsWith('.')) continue;\n      const packName = entry.name;\n      const packPath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}`;\n      const categories: Record<string, string[]> = {};\n\n      const manifest = await loadPackManifest(packName);\n      const hasManifest = await exists(`${packPath}/manifest.json`);\n\n      const catEntries = await readDir(packPath);\n      for (const cat of catEntries) {\n        if (!cat.isDirectory) continue;\n        if (cat.name === undefined || cat.name.startsWith('.')) continue;\n        const catName = cat.name;\n        const catPath = `${packPath}/${catName}`;\n        const fileEntries = await readDir(catPath);\n        const audioFiles = fileEntries\n          .filter((f) => !f.isDirectory && f.name !== undefined && hasAudioExtension(f.name))\n          .map((f) => f.name as string);\n        if (audioFiles.length > 0 || AGENT_EVENT_TYPES.includes(catName as AgentEventType)) {\n          categories[catName] = audioFiles.sort();\n        }\n      }\n\n      for (const eventType of AGENT_EVENT_TYPES) {\n        if (!(eventType in categories)) {\n          categories[eventType] = [];\n        }\n      }\n\n      discovered.push({ name: packName, categories, manifest, hasManifest });\n    }\n\n    packs.value = discovered;\n    return discovered;\n  }\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Sound override helpers (two-layer: soundOverrides → manifest default)\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  /** Extract filename from \"category/filename\" or plain \"filename\" key. */\n  function extractFilename(categoryAndFile: string): string {\n    const slashIdx = categoryAndFile.indexOf('/');\n    return slashIdx >= 0 ? categoryAndFile.slice(slashIdx + 1) : categoryAndFile;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Effective volume for a sound: soundOverrides → manifest default → 1.0\n   */\n  function effectiveVolume(packName: string, filename: string, manifestSound?: PackManifestSound): number {\n    const override = config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`];\n    if (override !== undefined) return override.volume;\n    return manifestSound?.volume ?? 1.0;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Effective enabled state: soundOverrides → manifest default → true\n   */\n  function isEnabled(packName: string, filename: string, manifestSound?: PackManifestSound): boolean {\n    const override = config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`];\n    if (override !== undefined) return override.enabled;\n    return manifestSound?.enabled ?? true;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Get track config for a sound. Accepts legacy \"category/filename\" key format.\n   * Reads from soundOverrides using packName/filename key.\n   */\n  function getTrackConfig(packName: string, categoryAndFile: string): TrackConfig {\n    const filename = extractFilename(categoryAndFile);\n    const override = config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`];\n    return override ?? { enabled: true, volume: 1.0 };\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Set track config for a sound. Accepts legacy \"category/filename\" key format.\n   * Writes to soundOverrides using packName/filename key.\n   */\n  function setTrackConfig(packName: string, categoryAndFile: string, track: TrackConfig): void {\n    const filename = extractFilename(categoryAndFile);\n    config.value.soundOverrides[`${packName}/${filename}`] = track;\n  }\n\n  function getSoundPacksDir(): string {\n    return soundPacksDir;\n  }\n\n  function getSessionPack(sessionId: string): string | undefined {\n    return sessionPacks.get(sessionId);\n  }\n\n  function assignSessionPack(sessionId: string, preferredPacks: string[]): void {\n    const pool = preferredPacks.length > 0 ? preferredPacks : config.value.activePacks;\n    if (pool.length === 0) return;\n    const chosen = pool[Math.floor(Math.random() * pool.length)];\n    if (chosen !== undefined) {\n      sessionPacks.set(sessionId, chosen);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // AudioContext helpers\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  function getAudioContext(): AudioContext {\n    if (!audioCtx) {\n      audioCtx = new AudioContext();\n    }\n    return audioCtx;\n  }\n\n  async function loadBuffer(filePath: string): Promise<AudioBuffer | null> {\n    const cached = bufferCache.get(filePath);\n    if (cached !== undefined) return cached;\n\n    try {\n      const bytes = await readFile(filePath);\n      const ctx = getAudioContext();\n      const buffer = await ctx.decodeAudioData(bytes.buffer as ArrayBuffer);\n      bufferCache.set(filePath, buffer);\n      return buffer;\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.warn(`[soundStore] Failed to decode audio: ${filePath}`, err);\n      return null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Playback engine\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  async function playForEvent(event: AgentEvent): Promise<void> {\n    if (!config.value.enabled) return;\n\n    // Session pack assignment on session_start\n    if (event.type === 'session_start') {\n      const { activePacks } = config.value;\n      if (activePacks.length > 0) {\n        const randomIdx = Math.floor(Math.random() * activePacks.length);\n        const chosen = activePacks[randomIdx];\n        if (chosen !== undefined) {\n          sessionPacks.set(event.sessionId, chosen);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    const packName = sessionPacks.get(event.sessionId);\n    if (!packName) return;\n\n    const category = event.type;\n    const now = Date.now();\n    const cooldownMs = config.value.cooldownSeconds * 1000;\n    const lastPlayed = cooldownMap.get(category) ?? 0;\n    if (now - lastPlayed < cooldownMs) return;\n\n    if (playing) return;\n\n    // Find the pack info\n    const packInfo = packs.value.find((p) => p.name === packName);\n    if (!packInfo) return;\n\n    // Look up manifest assignments for this event type\n    const assignedFiles = packInfo.manifest.assignments\n      .filter((a) => a.event === event.type)\n      .map((a) => a.file);\n\n    // Build a lookup map for manifest sound defaults\n    const manifestSoundMap = new Map(packInfo.manifest.sounds.map((s) => [s.file, s]));\n\n    // Filter to enabled files using two-layer rule (soundOverrides → manifest default)\n    const enabledFiles = assignedFiles.filter((filename) =>\n      isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename)),\n    );\n\n    if (enabledFiles.length === 0) return;\n\n    const randomFileIdx = Math.floor(Math.random() * enabledFiles.length);\n    const chosenFile = enabledFiles[randomFileIdx];\n    if (chosenFile === undefined) return;\n\n    // Files live at pack root, not in category subdirectories\n    const filePath = `${soundPacksDir}/${packName}/${chosenFile}`;\n\n    // Skip missing file with a warning — no crash\n    const fileOnDisk = await exists(filePath);\n    if (!fileOnDisk) {\n      console.warn(`[soundStore] Sound file not found on disk, skipping: ${filePath}`);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const buffer = await loadBuffer(filePath);\n    if (!buffer) return;\n\n    const manifestSound = manifestSoundMap.get(chosenFile);\n    const vol = effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound);\n    const ctx = getAudioContext();\n\n    const gainNode = ctx.createGain();\n    gainNode.gain.value = config.value.globalVolume * vol;\n    gainNode.connect(ctx.destination);\n\n    const source = ctx.createBufferSource();\n    source.buffer = buffer;\n    source.connect(gainNode);\n\n    playing = true;\n    cooldownMap.set(category, now);\n    lastPlayedSessionId.value = event.sessionId;\n\n    source.onended = () => {\n      playing = false;\n    };\n\n    source.start();\n  }\n\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // Public AudioContext access (for AudioPlayer.vue)\n  // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  function getOrCreateAudioContext(): AudioContext {\n    return getAudioContext();\n  }\n\n  function getBufferCache(): Map<string, AudioBuffer> {\n    return bufferCache;\n  }\n\n  return {\n    config,\n    packs,\n    lastPlayedSessionId,\n    init,\n    saveConfig,\n    scanPacks,\n    loadPackManifest,\n    savePackManifest,\n    getTrackConfig,\n    setTrackConfig,\n    effectiveVolume,\n    isEnabled,\n    getSoundPacksDir,\n    playForEvent,\n    getOrCreateAudioContext,\n    getBufferCache,\n    loadBuffer,\n    getSessionPack,\n    assignSessionPack,\n  };\n});\n","numLines":458,"startLine":1,"totalLines":458}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016friK1Gp5qVuc5weRCgBcD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the codebase. US-009 requires:\n\n1. Left column accepts file drag from OS (dragover + drop on column area)\n2. Dropped audio files (wav/mp3/ogg/flac/m4a/webm) are copied to pack directory root\n3. Dropped files are added to manifest.sounds with defaults: volume 1.0, enabled true\n4. Manifest autosaved after file add\n5. 'Add file' button above left column opens Tauri file picker (dialog plugin); selected files go through same flow\n6. Non-audio files dropped/selected are silently ignored or shown a brief error\n\n\n7. vue-tsc -b passes\n\nI need to add drag-and-drop handlers to the sounds column that are separate from the existing ZIP import handlers, then wire up an \"Add file\" button to open the file picker dialog. Both flows should copy audio files to the pack directory and update the manifest with the new sounds.\n\nFor OS drag-and-drop in Tauri's WebView, I can't get direct file paths from the dropped files, so I'll need to read the file content as bytes and write it to disk. The file picker approach is cleaner—I'll use the dialog plugin to get a path, then read and copy the file. I need to make sure the sounds column drop zone is distinct from the outer dialog's ZIP import handler so they don't interfere.\n\nMy plan is to add an \"Add file\" button and drop zone specifically for the sounds column, create a function to filter and import audio files, and use `stopPropagation` on the drop event to prevent it from bubbling up to the ZIP handler.\n\nNow I'm checking what's already imported in SoundsDialog - I have `readFile`, `writeFile`, `exists`, and `mkdir` from the file system plugin, plus `open` from the dialog plugin. For OS file drops, I'll use the File API's `arrayBuffer()` method to read the data, then write it with `writeFile`. For the file picker, I'll get the path from `open`, read the source file, and write it to the pack directory. I'll define the allowed audio extensions locally to keep things simple, then start implementing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17306,"cache_read_input_tokens":43699,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":17306},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cac4cc3a-a489-4a33-8e33-38a50ff4c60b","uuid":"de0cacee-0d73-47af-af3d-9823e34a4416"}
