{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015tW7hHZT62DLpfmMDAy2ra","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n     3→- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n     4→- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n     5→- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n     6→- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n     7→- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n     8→\n     9→---\n    10→\n    11→## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n    12→- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n    13→- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n    14→- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n    15→- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n    16→- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n    17→- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n    18→- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n    19→- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n    20→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    21→  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n    22→  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n    23→  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n    24→---\n    25→\n    26→## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n    27→- Replaced old category accordion panel with two-column patchbay layout (Sounds + Events)\n    28→- Left column shows \"Sounds\" header with empty body (US-005 will populate)\n    29→- Right column shows all 16 AgentEventType rows; dimmed (`opacity-40`) when no assignments, full opacity when assigned\n    30→- Removed dead code: `sortedCategories`, `categoryAllEnabled`, `toggleCategoryEnabled`, `toggleCategory`, `expandedCategories`, `addFilesToCategory`, `deleteTrack`, `getFilePath`, `AudioPlayer` import\n    31→- Kept `remove` and `copyFile` imports removed (will be re-added in US-005/US-009)\n    32→- `hasAssignments(eventType)` reads from `selectedPackInfo.manifest.assignments`\n    33→- Info popovers migrated from category-based to event-type-based (same pattern)\n    34→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    35→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    36→  - The prd.json lives in the main repo dir (`/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/`), NOT in the worktree — edit it there\n    37→  - `rightPanel` ref now wraps the entire two-column area (the `flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden` div) — scroll reset via `rightPanel.scrollTop = 0` is preserved\n    38→  - The `confirmCreatePack` still creates old-style event subdirectories — US-010 will fix this to use manifest\n    39→---\n    40→\n    41→## 2026-03-04 - US-005\n    42→- Implemented left column sound file list with inline preview\n    43→- Each sound row: play button (▶), filename, broken-link indicator (⚠ in red), volume slider (on hover), enabled toggle (checkbox), stop button (■ active when playing)\n    44→- `playPreview(filename)` uses soundStore.loadBuffer + getOrCreateAudioContext, stops any current source first (restarts from start)\n    45→- `stopPreview()` stops the AudioBufferSourceNode safely (try/catch for already-stopped)\n    46→- `checkSoundFileExistence(packName)` async parallel check using `exists()` from plugin-fs, results in `soundFileExists` Map\n    47→- `updateSoundVolume/updateSoundEnabled` mutate the manifest.sounds entry in place (reactive through Pinia ref), then call `savePackManifest`\n    48→- Hover state tracked with `hoveredSoundFile` ref; volume slider uses `v-show` for visibility\n    49→- `watch(selectedPack)` extended: stops preview, clears existence map, triggers new existence check, resets scroll\n    50→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    51→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    52→  - `AudioBufferSourceNode.stop()` can throw if already stopped — always wrap in try/catch\n    53→  - `soundFileExists.value` must be a `ref<Map<...>>` not a reactive Map for `v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(x) === false\"` to be reactive\n    54→  - Mutating nested objects inside `packs.value[i].manifest.sounds[j]` IS reactive (Pinia wraps deeply)\n    55→  - `exists` must be imported from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` (already available in soundStore)\n    56→  - prd.json may have extra fields like `\"inProgress\": true` — clean them up when setting passes: true\n    57→---\n    58→\n    59→## 2026-03-04 - US-006\n    60→- Implemented event row sound chips in the right column of the patchbay\n    61→- Each event row shows chips for assigned sound files with truncated filenames (max 20 chars + ellipsis)\n    62→- Chip body click plays a preview (reuses existing `playPreview` function)\n    63→- Chip × button removes the `(file, event)` assignment from manifest and autosaves\n    64→- Live highlight: listens to `agent-event` Tauri events; matching event row flashes with `bg-indigo-600/30` for 200ms\n    65→- Event row layout changed from single flex row to stacked: header row + chips row below\n    66→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    67→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    68→  - `listen` from `@tauri-apps/api/event` can be used in any component, not just RunView — import + onUnmounted cleanup\n    69→  - The Tauri event payload for `agent-event` is a JSON string that needs `JSON.parse` → `AgentEvent`\n    70→  - `flashingEvent` ref + `setTimeout(200ms)` pattern works well for brief UI flash effects\n    71→  - Cleaned up `\"inProgress\": true` from prd.json when setting `passes: true`\n    72→---\n    73→\n    74→## 2026-03-04 - US-007\n    75→- Implemented drag-and-drop from sound rows (left column) to event rows (right column)\n    76→- Sound rows are `draggable=\"true\"` with `cursor-grab` and dim to `opacity-50` while being dragged\n    77→- Event rows accept drops via `@dragover`, `@dragleave`, `@drop` handlers\n    78→- During drag: all event rows become full opacity (visible as drop targets), hovered row gets `bg-indigo-500/20` highlight\n    79→- `addAssignment(file, eventType)` checks for duplicates before pushing to manifest and autosaving\n    80→- HTML5 Drag API: `effectAllowed: 'copy'`, `dropEffect: 'copy'`, `setData('text/plain', filename)` for native ghost\n    81→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    82→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    83→  - HTML5 drag ghost (default browser behavior) shows a translucent copy of the dragged element — no custom ghost needed for basic cases\n    84→  - `draggingSoundFile` ref tracks drag state; cleared in both `dragend` and `drop` handlers for safety\n    85→  - All event rows get `opacity-100` during drag via conditional class to override the dimmed state for unassigned events\n    86→  - `e.preventDefault()` in `dragover` is required to make an element a valid drop target\n    87→---\n    88→\n    89→## 2026-03-04 - US-008\n    90→- Implemented chip-to-sound-row drag-and-drop for re-assigning events to different sounds\n    91→- Assignment chips are `draggable=\"true\"` with `@dragstart.stop` (stop prevents parent event row from also starting a drag)\n    92→- `draggingChip` ref tracks `{ file, event }` during drag; `dragOverSoundFile` tracks hovered sound row\n    93→- Sound rows accept drops via `@dragover`, `@dragleave`, `@drop` handlers (only active when `draggingChip` is set)\n    94→- `onSoundRowDrop`: removes old `(originalFile, event)` assignment, adds `(newFile, event)` if not already present; autosaves\n    95→- Same-sound drop is silently ignored (`chip.file === newFile` early return)\n    96→- Visual feedback: sound rows get `bg-indigo-500/20` highlight during chip drag hover, all rows full opacity\n    97→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n    98→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    99→  - Use `@dragstart.stop` on chips to prevent the parent event row div from also receiving the dragstart event\n   100→  - Two separate drag modes coexist: `draggingSoundFile` (sound→event) and `draggingChip` (chip→sound) — guard handlers with the appropriate ref check\n   101→  - `effectAllowed: 'move'` for chip drag vs `'copy'` for sound drag distinguishes intent visually in the browser\n   102→---\n   103→\n   104→## 2026-03-04 - US-009\n   105→- Implemented OS file drag-and-drop onto the sounds column to add audio files to a pack\n   106→- Implemented \"Add file\" button in sounds column header that opens Tauri file picker (multiple selection, audio filter)\n   107→- Audio files (wav/mp3/ogg/flac/m4a/webm) are copied to pack directory root via `writeFile`\n   108→- New files added to `manifest.sounds` with defaults `{ volume: 1.0, enabled: true }`; duplicates skipped\n   109→- Non-audio files silently ignored (filtered by extension check)\n   110→- Drop overlay shows \"Drop audio files here\" on the sounds column during OS drag\n   111→- `e.stopPropagation()` on sounds column drop handlers prevents the outer dialog ZIP import handler from catching audio file drops\n   112→- `checkSoundFileExistence` called after adding files to refresh the existence map\n   113→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n   114→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   115→  - OS file drops in WebView use `File.arrayBuffer()` to get bytes (same as ZIP import), then `writeFile` to copy to pack dir\n   116→  - `open({ multiple: true })` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog` returns `string[] | null` for multi-select\n   117→  - Use `e.stopPropagation()` on inner drop zones to prevent outer drop handlers from also firing\n   118→  - Three drag modes now coexist: `draggingSoundFile` (sound→event), `draggingChip` (chip→sound), `audioDragOver` (OS→sounds column)\n   119→---\n   120→\n   121→## 2026-03-04 - US-010\n   122→- Replaced old \"type name first, then create\" flow with immediate create + inline rename\n   123→- `startCreatePack()` generates unique name (\"New Pack\", \"New Pack 2\", etc.), creates dir, writes empty manifest.json, scans, selects, enters inline edit mode\n   124→- Inline edit: pack entry in sidebar shows `<input>` when `editingPackName` matches the pack name\n   125→- Enter/blur → `confirmEditPackName()`: renames directory on disk, updates activePacks + soundOverrides, rescans\n   126→- Escape → `cancelEditPackName()`: if `isNewPack`, deletes the directory and rescans\n   127→- Removed old `creatingPack`, `newPackName`, `newPackInput` refs and the input-above-buttons UI\n   128→- Added `rename` and `remove` imports from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs`\n   129→- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n   130→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   131→  - `ref` on a `v-if` element inside a `v-for` loop resolves to the single visible instance when only one matches — works fine for inline edit\n   132→  - `@keydown.escape.prevent` is important to prevent Escape from bubbling to the dialog close handler\n   133→  - Rename logic mirrors PackContextMenu.confirmRename — keep them in sync if changing soundOverrides migration\n   134→  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n   135→---\n   136→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aad13967-80bc-4110-aefd-964e65e8c225","uuid":"45b7ce88-c14a-498d-b13c-8c3568d0cf1b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n- Replaced old category accordion panel with two-column patchbay layout (Sounds + Events)\n- Left column shows \"Sounds\" header with empty body (US-005 will populate)\n- Right column shows all 16 AgentEventType rows; dimmed (`opacity-40`) when no assignments, full opacity when assigned\n- Removed dead code: `sortedCategories`, `categoryAllEnabled`, `toggleCategoryEnabled`, `toggleCategory`, `expandedCategories`, `addFilesToCategory`, `deleteTrack`, `getFilePath`, `AudioPlayer` import\n- Kept `remove` and `copyFile` imports removed (will be re-added in US-005/US-009)\n- `hasAssignments(eventType)` reads from `selectedPackInfo.manifest.assignments`\n- Info popovers migrated from category-based to event-type-based (same pattern)\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The prd.json lives in the main repo dir (`/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/`), NOT in the worktree — edit it there\n  - `rightPanel` ref now wraps the entire two-column area (the `flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden` div) — scroll reset via `rightPanel.scrollTop = 0` is preserved\n  - The `confirmCreatePack` still creates old-style event subdirectories — US-010 will fix this to use manifest\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-005\n- Implemented left column sound file list with inline preview\n- Each sound row: play button (▶), filename, broken-link indicator (⚠ in red), volume slider (on hover), enabled toggle (checkbox), stop button (■ active when playing)\n- `playPreview(filename)` uses soundStore.loadBuffer + getOrCreateAudioContext, stops any current source first (restarts from start)\n- `stopPreview()` stops the AudioBufferSourceNode safely (try/catch for already-stopped)\n- `checkSoundFileExistence(packName)` async parallel check using `exists()` from plugin-fs, results in `soundFileExists` Map\n- `updateSoundVolume/updateSoundEnabled` mutate the manifest.sounds entry in place (reactive through Pinia ref), then call `savePackManifest`\n- Hover state tracked with `hoveredSoundFile` ref; volume slider uses `v-show` for visibility\n- `watch(selectedPack)` extended: stops preview, clears existence map, triggers new existence check, resets scroll\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `AudioBufferSourceNode.stop()` can throw if already stopped — always wrap in try/catch\n  - `soundFileExists.value` must be a `ref<Map<...>>` not a reactive Map for `v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(x) === false\"` to be reactive\n  - Mutating nested objects inside `packs.value[i].manifest.sounds[j]` IS reactive (Pinia wraps deeply)\n  - `exists` must be imported from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` (already available in soundStore)\n  - prd.json may have extra fields like `\"inProgress\": true` — clean them up when setting passes: true\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-006\n- Implemented event row sound chips in the right column of the patchbay\n- Each event row shows chips for assigned sound files with truncated filenames (max 20 chars + ellipsis)\n- Chip body click plays a preview (reuses existing `playPreview` function)\n- Chip × button removes the `(file, event)` assignment from manifest and autosaves\n- Live highlight: listens to `agent-event` Tauri events; matching event row flashes with `bg-indigo-600/30` for 200ms\n- Event row layout changed from single flex row to stacked: header row + chips row below\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `listen` from `@tauri-apps/api/event` can be used in any component, not just RunView — import + onUnmounted cleanup\n  - The Tauri event payload for `agent-event` is a JSON string that needs `JSON.parse` → `AgentEvent`\n  - `flashingEvent` ref + `setTimeout(200ms)` pattern works well for brief UI flash effects\n  - Cleaned up `\"inProgress\": true` from prd.json when setting `passes: true`\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-007\n- Implemented drag-and-drop from sound rows (left column) to event rows (right column)\n- Sound rows are `draggable=\"true\"` with `cursor-grab` and dim to `opacity-50` while being dragged\n- Event rows accept drops via `@dragover`, `@dragleave`, `@drop` handlers\n- During drag: all event rows become full opacity (visible as drop targets), hovered row gets `bg-indigo-500/20` highlight\n- `addAssignment(file, eventType)` checks for duplicates before pushing to manifest and autosaving\n- HTML5 Drag API: `effectAllowed: 'copy'`, `dropEffect: 'copy'`, `setData('text/plain', filename)` for native ghost\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - HTML5 drag ghost (default browser behavior) shows a translucent copy of the dragged element — no custom ghost needed for basic cases\n  - `draggingSoundFile` ref tracks drag state; cleared in both `dragend` and `drop` handlers for safety\n  - All event rows get `opacity-100` during drag via conditional class to override the dimmed state for unassigned events\n  - `e.preventDefault()` in `dragover` is required to make an element a valid drop target\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-008\n- Implemented chip-to-sound-row drag-and-drop for re-assigning events to different sounds\n- Assignment chips are `draggable=\"true\"` with `@dragstart.stop` (stop prevents parent event row from also starting a drag)\n- `draggingChip` ref tracks `{ file, event }` during drag; `dragOverSoundFile` tracks hovered sound row\n- Sound rows accept drops via `@dragover`, `@dragleave`, `@drop` handlers (only active when `draggingChip` is set)\n- `onSoundRowDrop`: removes old `(originalFile, event)` assignment, adds `(newFile, event)` if not already present; autosaves\n- Same-sound drop is silently ignored (`chip.file === newFile` early return)\n- Visual feedback: sound rows get `bg-indigo-500/20` highlight during chip drag hover, all rows full opacity\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Use `@dragstart.stop` on chips to prevent the parent event row div from also receiving the dragstart event\n  - Two separate drag modes coexist: `draggingSoundFile` (sound→event) and `draggingChip` (chip→sound) — guard handlers with the appropriate ref check\n  - `effectAllowed: 'move'` for chip drag vs `'copy'` for sound drag distinguishes intent visually in the browser\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-009\n- Implemented OS file drag-and-drop onto the sounds column to add audio files to a pack\n- Implemented \"Add file\" button in sounds column header that opens Tauri file picker (multiple selection, audio filter)\n- Audio files (wav/mp3/ogg/flac/m4a/webm) are copied to pack directory root via `writeFile`\n- New files added to `manifest.sounds` with defaults `{ volume: 1.0, enabled: true }`; duplicates skipped\n- Non-audio files silently ignored (filtered by extension check)\n- Drop overlay shows \"Drop audio files here\" on the sounds column during OS drag\n- `e.stopPropagation()` on sounds column drop handlers prevents the outer dialog ZIP import handler from catching audio file drops\n- `checkSoundFileExistence` called after adding files to refresh the existence map\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - OS file drops in WebView use `File.arrayBuffer()` to get bytes (same as ZIP import), then `writeFile` to copy to pack dir\n  - `open({ multiple: true })` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog` returns `string[] | null` for multi-select\n  - Use `e.stopPropagation()` on inner drop zones to prevent outer drop handlers from also firing\n  - Three drag modes now coexist: `draggingSoundFile` (sound→event), `draggingChip` (chip→sound), `audioDragOver` (OS→sounds column)\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-010\n- Replaced old \"type name first, then create\" flow with immediate create + inline rename\n- `startCreatePack()` generates unique name (\"New Pack\", \"New Pack 2\", etc.), creates dir, writes empty manifest.json, scans, selects, enters inline edit mode\n- Inline edit: pack entry in sidebar shows `<input>` when `editingPackName` matches the pack name\n- Enter/blur → `confirmEditPackName()`: renames directory on disk, updates activePacks + soundOverrides, rescans\n- Escape → `cancelEditPackName()`: if `isNewPack`, deletes the directory and rescans\n- Removed old `creatingPack`, `newPackName`, `newPackInput` refs and the input-above-buttons UI\n- Added `rename` and `remove` imports from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs`\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `ref` on a `v-if` element inside a `v-for` loop resolves to the single visible instance when only one matches — works fine for inline edit\n  - `@keydown.escape.prevent` is important to prevent Escape from bubbling to the dialog close handler\n  - Rename logic mirrors PackContextMenu.confirmRename — keep them in sync if changing soundOverrides migration\n  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n---\n","numLines":136,"startLine":1,"totalLines":136}}}
