{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017qJ7f4jv55M1FveRvcL7Hn","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/prd.json has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aad13967-80bc-4110-aefd-964e65e8c225","uuid":"ae84e09f-dd4a-428c-bacc-5fbe53a806a8","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/prd.json","oldString":"      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"inProgress\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-012\",","newString":"      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-012\",","originalFile":"{\n  \"project\": \"Sound Pack Patchbay Editor\",\n  \"description\": \"Redesign the SoundsDialog interior to a patchbay model: a split-view editor where sound files (left column) are explicitly wired to agent events (right column) via drag-and-drop. Replaces the implicit folder-name-to-event-type encoding with an explicit manifest.json per pack. Eliminates the need to copy audio files across event folders when one sound should serve multiple events.\",\n  \"userStories\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n      \"title\": \"manifest.json schema + read/write in soundStore\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the soundStore to read and write manifest.json from each pack directory so the patchbay has a persistent source of truth.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"PackManifest TypeScript interface: { sounds: Array\\u003c{ file: string, volume: number, enabled: boolean }\\u003e, assignments: Array\\u003c{ file: string, event: AgentEventType }\\u003e }\",\n        \"soundStore.loadPackManifest(packName) reads manifest.json from pack directory; returns empty manifest if file missing\",\n        \"soundStore.savePackManifest(packName, manifest) writes manifest.json to pack directory\",\n        \"soundStore.scanPacks() updated: scans pack directories for audio files AND reads manifest.json; PackInfo includes manifest data\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n      \"title\": \"config.json migration — soundOverrides replaces tracks\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the config schema updated to store per-sound overrides by pack/filename key instead of category/filename.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"SoundConfig.soundOverrides: Record\\u003cstring, { volume: number, enabled: boolean }\\u003e where key is '\\u003cpackName\\u003e/\\u003cfilename\\u003e'\",\n        \"Old SoundConfig.tracks key still accepted on read (backward compat); migrated to soundOverrides on next write\",\n        \"effectiveVolume and isEnabled resolution follows the two-layer rule: soundOverrides → manifest default\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n      \"title\": \"playForEvent updated for manifest-based lookup\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want sounds to play based on manifest assignments so my patchbay configuration is reflected in runtime audio.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"playForEvent(event) looks up active pack for session → reads manifest.assignments filtered by event.type → collects enabled files → picks random → plays\",\n        \"Volume resolved via two-layer rule (US-002)\",\n        \"Missing file (in manifest but not on disk) is skipped with a console warning — no crash\",\n        \"Per-event cooldown still applies\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n      \"title\": \"SoundsDialog — patchbay split view layout\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want the SoundsDialog content area to show a two-column patchbay so I can see sounds and events side by side.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Dialog content area (right of pack sidebar) splits into two equal columns\",\n        \"Left column header: 'Sounds', right column header: 'Events'\",\n        \"Right column shows all 16 AgentEventType values as rows\",\n        \"Event rows with no assignments are visually dimmed (reduced opacity or lighter text)\",\n        \"Event rows with assignments are full-opacity\",\n        \"Pack sidebar and context menu unchanged\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n      \"title\": \"Left column — sound file list with inline preview\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see all audio files in the selected pack and preview them inline.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Left column lists all files from manifest.sounds for selected pack\",\n        \"Each row shows: play button (left), raw filename, stop button (right)\",\n        \"Click play: loads and plays audio from start; if already playing, restarts from start\",\n        \"Click stop: stops current playback\",\n        \"Per-sound volume slider visible on hover\",\n        \"Per-sound enabled toggle (checkbox or switch) on each row\",\n        \"Changes to volume/enabled autosave: update manifest.sounds entry + write manifest.json\",\n        \"Missing file (in manifest but not on disk) shows red broken-link icon on row\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n      \"title\": \"Right column — event rows with sound chips\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want each event row to show which sounds are assigned as removable chips.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Each event row shows chips for all assigned sound files\",\n        \"Chip label: truncated filename (max ~20 chars with ellipsis)\",\n        \"Chip has × button; click × removes the (file, event) assignment from manifest and autosaves\",\n        \"Click chip body (not ×) plays a preview of that sound inline\",\n        \"Live highlight: when AgentEvent fires matching an event type while dialog is open, that event row briefly flashes (200ms highlight animation)\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n      \"title\": \"Drag sound from left column to event row\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to drag a sound file and drop it onto an event row to create an assignment.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Sound rows in left column are draggable (HTML5 drag API or equivalent)\",\n        \"During drag: ghost chip (translucent copy of filename chip) follows cursor\",\n        \"During drag: valid drop targets (event rows) highlight on hover\",\n        \"Drop onto event row: adds (file, event) to manifest.assignments if not already present; autosaves\",\n        \"Drop on duplicate (same file already assigned to same event): silently ignored, no feedback\",\n        \"Drop outside valid target: no change\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n      \"title\": \"Drag chip from event row to re-assign to different sound\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to drag an assignment chip from an event row and drop it onto a different sound in the left column to re-assign it.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Assignment chips in right column are draggable\",\n        \"During drag: ghost chip follows cursor; left column sound rows highlight as valid targets\",\n        \"Drop onto sound row: removes old (originalFile, event) assignment, adds (newFile, event) assignment; autosaves\",\n        \"Drop onto same sound row (no-op): silently ignored\",\n        \"Drop outside valid target: no change, assignment remains\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n      \"title\": \"Add audio files to pack — drag from Finder + file picker\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to add new audio files to a pack via drag-and-drop or file picker.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Left column accepts file drag from OS (dragover + drop on column area)\",\n        \"Dropped audio files (wav/mp3/ogg/flac/m4a/webm) are copied to pack directory root\",\n        \"Dropped files are added to manifest.sounds with defaults: volume 1.0, enabled true\",\n        \"Manifest autosaved after file add\",\n        \"'Add file' button above left column opens Tauri file picker (dialog plugin); selected files go through same flow\",\n        \"Non-audio files dropped/selected are silently ignored or shown a brief error\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n      \"title\": \"Pack creation — immediate create with inline rename\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to create a new pack that appears immediately with an editable name.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Clicking + in pack sidebar creates a pack directory with generated name ('New Pack', 'New Pack 2', etc.)\",\n        \"Empty manifest.json written to new pack directory immediately\",\n        \"Pack name field enters inline edit mode with cursor focused\",\n        \"Enter or blur confirms name; renames directory on disk\",\n        \"Escape cancels and deletes the newly created pack (since it's empty and user aborted naming)\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n      \"title\": \"ZIP import — manifest.json required\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to import sound packs from ZIP files that use the new manifest format.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"ZIP import reads manifest.json from pack root inside ZIP\",\n        \"If manifest.json is absent, import fails with error message: 'This ZIP does not contain a manifest.json. Please use the new pack format.'\",\n        \"Audio files are extracted to pack directory root (not into subdirectories)\",\n        \"manifest.json is written to pack directory\",\n        \"Pack appears in sidebar after import\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"inProgress\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n      \"title\": \"Old pack migration — 'Migrate to new format' in context menu\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to migrate old folder-structured packs to the new manifest format without losing my configuration.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Packs without manifest.json detected on scan; labeled with a migration indicator in the sidebar\",\n        \"Pack context menu shows 'Migrate to new format' option for old-style packs\",\n        \"Migration: reads all audio files from subdirectories, creates assignments from folder names (folder name → event type), moves files to pack root, writes manifest.json, removes old subdirectories\",\n        \"After migration, indicator removed and pack is fully functional in patchbay\",\n        \"vue-tsc -b passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"passes\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":167,"oldLines":8,"newStart":167,"newLines":7,"lines":["         \"vue-tsc -b passes\"","       ],","       \"priority\": 6,","-      \"passes\": false,","-      \"inProgress\": true","+      \"passes\": true","     },","     {","       \"id\": \"US-012\","]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014w4QsiG6svXE1MXCbngF2Q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now append progress to progress.md:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":69627,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aad13967-80bc-4110-aefd-964e65e8c225","uuid":"43dceea6-5cb9-493b-9db7-579344722ea7"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014w4QsiG6svXE1MXCbngF2Q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0146cuoWAZzGegZer8qPSoBx","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md","old_string":"  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n---","new_string":"  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-011\n- Updated `importZipBytes` to require manifest.json in ZIP; shows error toast if missing\n- ZIP can have manifest at root or inside a single top-level folder (common ZIP structure) — `stripPrefix` handles both\n- Audio files extracted flat to pack root (no subdirectories preserved)\n- manifest.json written to pack directory before audio files\n- Added `importError` ref + `showImportError()` with 5s auto-dismiss toast at top of dialog\n- Non-manifest files in subdirectories are skipped (`effectivePath.includes('/')` guard)\n- Cleaned up `importErrorTimeout` in `onUnmounted`\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - JSZip `zip.file('path')` returns null if the file doesn't exist — use it to check for manifest presence\n  - Common ZIP tools wrap files in a single top-level folder matching the ZIP filename — handle `stripPrefix` for that case\n  - `showImportError` pattern with auto-dismiss timeout is reusable for other transient error messages in dialogs\n---"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":69627,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aad13967-80bc-4110-aefd-964e65e8c225","uuid":"3f66f96a-0c18-4fa2-ae25-a80258308635"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0146cuoWAZzGegZer8qPSoBx","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aad13967-80bc-4110-aefd-964e65e8c225","uuid":"3ad60803-b8e2-4038-80ef-c230d81b4723","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md","oldString":"  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n---","newString":"  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-011\n- Updated `importZipBytes` to require manifest.json in ZIP; shows error toast if missing\n- ZIP can have manifest at root or inside a single top-level folder (common ZIP structure) — `stripPrefix` handles both\n- Audio files extracted flat to pack root (no subdirectories preserved)\n- manifest.json written to pack directory before audio files\n- Added `importError` ref + `showImportError()` with 5s auto-dismiss toast at top of dialog\n- Non-manifest files in subdirectories are skipped (`effectivePath.includes('/')` guard)\n- Cleaned up `importErrorTimeout` in `onUnmounted`\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - JSZip `zip.file('path')` returns null if the file doesn't exist — use it to check for manifest presence\n  - Common ZIP tools wrap files in a single top-level folder matching the ZIP filename — handle `stripPrefix` for that case\n  - `showImportError` pattern with auto-dismiss timeout is reusable for other transient error messages in dialogs\n---","originalFile":"## Codebase Patterns\n- `soundStore.ts` is in `src/stores/` and uses Pinia defineStore with composition API style\n- `PackInfo` has both legacy `categories: Record<string, string[]>` (folder-based) and `manifest: PackManifest` (new)\n- Two-layer volume/enabled resolution: `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` — both are already in soundStore\n- Files in new manifest-based packs live at pack root (`soundPacksDir/packName/filename`), not in category subdirectories\n- `exists` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` is already imported in soundStore for file existence checks\n- Type check via `bun run build` (runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build`)\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n- Updated `playForEvent` to use manifest-based lookup instead of folder-based categories\n- Now reads `packInfo.manifest.assignments.filter(a => a.event === event.type)` to get assigned files\n- Builds `manifestSoundMap` from `packInfo.manifest.sounds` for volume/enabled defaults\n- Filters enabled files using `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSoundMap.get(filename))`\n- Resolves volume using `effectiveVolume(packName, chosenFile, manifestSound)`\n- File path changed from `soundPacksDir/packName/category/file` to `soundPacksDir/packName/file`\n- Added `exists()` check before loading — skips with `console.warn` if file not on disk\n- **Files changed:** `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The old `categories` field on PackInfo is still populated by scanPacks but is no longer used in playback — it remains for legacy/UI purposes\n  - Session pack assignment on `session_start` is still inline in `playForEvent` (separate from `assignSessionPack` which handles preferred packs from Character)\n  - `getTrackConfig` / `setTrackConfig` still exist for backward compat but playForEvent no longer uses them\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n- Replaced old category accordion panel with two-column patchbay layout (Sounds + Events)\n- Left column shows \"Sounds\" header with empty body (US-005 will populate)\n- Right column shows all 16 AgentEventType rows; dimmed (`opacity-40`) when no assignments, full opacity when assigned\n- Removed dead code: `sortedCategories`, `categoryAllEnabled`, `toggleCategoryEnabled`, `toggleCategory`, `expandedCategories`, `addFilesToCategory`, `deleteTrack`, `getFilePath`, `AudioPlayer` import\n- Kept `remove` and `copyFile` imports removed (will be re-added in US-005/US-009)\n- `hasAssignments(eventType)` reads from `selectedPackInfo.manifest.assignments`\n- Info popovers migrated from category-based to event-type-based (same pattern)\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The prd.json lives in the main repo dir (`/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/`), NOT in the worktree — edit it there\n  - `rightPanel` ref now wraps the entire two-column area (the `flex flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden` div) — scroll reset via `rightPanel.scrollTop = 0` is preserved\n  - The `confirmCreatePack` still creates old-style event subdirectories — US-010 will fix this to use manifest\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-005\n- Implemented left column sound file list with inline preview\n- Each sound row: play button (▶), filename, broken-link indicator (⚠ in red), volume slider (on hover), enabled toggle (checkbox), stop button (■ active when playing)\n- `playPreview(filename)` uses soundStore.loadBuffer + getOrCreateAudioContext, stops any current source first (restarts from start)\n- `stopPreview()` stops the AudioBufferSourceNode safely (try/catch for already-stopped)\n- `checkSoundFileExistence(packName)` async parallel check using `exists()` from plugin-fs, results in `soundFileExists` Map\n- `updateSoundVolume/updateSoundEnabled` mutate the manifest.sounds entry in place (reactive through Pinia ref), then call `savePackManifest`\n- Hover state tracked with `hoveredSoundFile` ref; volume slider uses `v-show` for visibility\n- `watch(selectedPack)` extended: stops preview, clears existence map, triggers new existence check, resets scroll\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `AudioBufferSourceNode.stop()` can throw if already stopped — always wrap in try/catch\n  - `soundFileExists.value` must be a `ref<Map<...>>` not a reactive Map for `v-if=\"soundFileExists.get(x) === false\"` to be reactive\n  - Mutating nested objects inside `packs.value[i].manifest.sounds[j]` IS reactive (Pinia wraps deeply)\n  - `exists` must be imported from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs` (already available in soundStore)\n  - prd.json may have extra fields like `\"inProgress\": true` — clean them up when setting passes: true\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-006\n- Implemented event row sound chips in the right column of the patchbay\n- Each event row shows chips for assigned sound files with truncated filenames (max 20 chars + ellipsis)\n- Chip body click plays a preview (reuses existing `playPreview` function)\n- Chip × button removes the `(file, event)` assignment from manifest and autosaves\n- Live highlight: listens to `agent-event` Tauri events; matching event row flashes with `bg-indigo-600/30` for 200ms\n- Event row layout changed from single flex row to stacked: header row + chips row below\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `listen` from `@tauri-apps/api/event` can be used in any component, not just RunView — import + onUnmounted cleanup\n  - The Tauri event payload for `agent-event` is a JSON string that needs `JSON.parse` → `AgentEvent`\n  - `flashingEvent` ref + `setTimeout(200ms)` pattern works well for brief UI flash effects\n  - Cleaned up `\"inProgress\": true` from prd.json when setting `passes: true`\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-007\n- Implemented drag-and-drop from sound rows (left column) to event rows (right column)\n- Sound rows are `draggable=\"true\"` with `cursor-grab` and dim to `opacity-50` while being dragged\n- Event rows accept drops via `@dragover`, `@dragleave`, `@drop` handlers\n- During drag: all event rows become full opacity (visible as drop targets), hovered row gets `bg-indigo-500/20` highlight\n- `addAssignment(file, eventType)` checks for duplicates before pushing to manifest and autosaving\n- HTML5 Drag API: `effectAllowed: 'copy'`, `dropEffect: 'copy'`, `setData('text/plain', filename)` for native ghost\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - HTML5 drag ghost (default browser behavior) shows a translucent copy of the dragged element — no custom ghost needed for basic cases\n  - `draggingSoundFile` ref tracks drag state; cleared in both `dragend` and `drop` handlers for safety\n  - All event rows get `opacity-100` during drag via conditional class to override the dimmed state for unassigned events\n  - `e.preventDefault()` in `dragover` is required to make an element a valid drop target\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-008\n- Implemented chip-to-sound-row drag-and-drop for re-assigning events to different sounds\n- Assignment chips are `draggable=\"true\"` with `@dragstart.stop` (stop prevents parent event row from also starting a drag)\n- `draggingChip` ref tracks `{ file, event }` during drag; `dragOverSoundFile` tracks hovered sound row\n- Sound rows accept drops via `@dragover`, `@dragleave`, `@drop` handlers (only active when `draggingChip` is set)\n- `onSoundRowDrop`: removes old `(originalFile, event)` assignment, adds `(newFile, event)` if not already present; autosaves\n- Same-sound drop is silently ignored (`chip.file === newFile` early return)\n- Visual feedback: sound rows get `bg-indigo-500/20` highlight during chip drag hover, all rows full opacity\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Use `@dragstart.stop` on chips to prevent the parent event row div from also receiving the dragstart event\n  - Two separate drag modes coexist: `draggingSoundFile` (sound→event) and `draggingChip` (chip→sound) — guard handlers with the appropriate ref check\n  - `effectAllowed: 'move'` for chip drag vs `'copy'` for sound drag distinguishes intent visually in the browser\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-009\n- Implemented OS file drag-and-drop onto the sounds column to add audio files to a pack\n- Implemented \"Add file\" button in sounds column header that opens Tauri file picker (multiple selection, audio filter)\n- Audio files (wav/mp3/ogg/flac/m4a/webm) are copied to pack directory root via `writeFile`\n- New files added to `manifest.sounds` with defaults `{ volume: 1.0, enabled: true }`; duplicates skipped\n- Non-audio files silently ignored (filtered by extension check)\n- Drop overlay shows \"Drop audio files here\" on the sounds column during OS drag\n- `e.stopPropagation()` on sounds column drop handlers prevents the outer dialog ZIP import handler from catching audio file drops\n- `checkSoundFileExistence` called after adding files to refresh the existence map\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - OS file drops in WebView use `File.arrayBuffer()` to get bytes (same as ZIP import), then `writeFile` to copy to pack dir\n  - `open({ multiple: true })` from `@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog` returns `string[] | null` for multi-select\n  - Use `e.stopPropagation()` on inner drop zones to prevent outer drop handlers from also firing\n  - Three drag modes now coexist: `draggingSoundFile` (sound→event), `draggingChip` (chip→sound), `audioDragOver` (OS→sounds column)\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-010\n- Replaced old \"type name first, then create\" flow with immediate create + inline rename\n- `startCreatePack()` generates unique name (\"New Pack\", \"New Pack 2\", etc.), creates dir, writes empty manifest.json, scans, selects, enters inline edit mode\n- Inline edit: pack entry in sidebar shows `<input>` when `editingPackName` matches the pack name\n- Enter/blur → `confirmEditPackName()`: renames directory on disk, updates activePacks + soundOverrides, rescans\n- Escape → `cancelEditPackName()`: if `isNewPack`, deletes the directory and rescans\n- Removed old `creatingPack`, `newPackName`, `newPackInput` refs and the input-above-buttons UI\n- Added `rename` and `remove` imports from `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs`\n- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `ref` on a `v-if` element inside a `v-for` loop resolves to the single visible instance when only one matches — works fine for inline edit\n  - `@keydown.escape.prevent` is important to prevent Escape from bubbling to the dialog close handler\n  - Rename logic mirrors PackContextMenu.confirmRename — keep them in sync if changing soundOverrides migration\n  - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)\n---\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":133,"oldLines":3,"newStart":133,"newLines":18,"lines":["   - Rename logic mirrors PackContextMenu.confirmRename — keep them in sync if changing soundOverrides migration","   - Old `confirmCreatePack` was creating event subdirectories — new flow writes only manifest.json (correct for patchbay model)"," ---","+","+## 2026-03-04 - US-011","+- Updated `importZipBytes` to require manifest.json in ZIP; shows error toast if missing","+- ZIP can have manifest at root or inside a single top-level folder (common ZIP structure) — `stripPrefix` handles both","+- Audio files extracted flat to pack root (no subdirectories preserved)","+- manifest.json written to pack directory before audio files","+- Added `importError` ref + `showImportError()` with 5s auto-dismiss toast at top of dialog","+- Non-manifest files in subdirectories are skipped (`effectivePath.includes('/')` guard)","+- Cleaned up `importErrorTimeout` in `onUnmounted`","+- **Files changed:** `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`","+- **Learnings for future iterations:**","+  - JSZip `zip.file('path')` returns null if the file doesn't exist — use it to check for manifest presence","+  - Common ZIP tools wrap files in a single top-level folder matching the ZIP filename — handle `stripPrefix` for that case","+  - `showImportError` pattern with auto-dismiss timeout is reusable for other transient error messages in dialogs","+---"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
